Cut small pieces of black licorice for each eye and eyebrow; position on clown's face. Outline smile with red licorice strap; spread red butter cream inside smile, repeat for cheeks. Place small strip of black licorice inside smile.

Position large gum balls for nose and bow-tie `knot'; place small gum balls on hat. Outline bow-tie with red licorice straps. Make three-petalled daisy at top of hat with a piece of red licorice strap and a small gum ball.

title: chicken burger with pickled cucumber and wasabi mayonnaise
directions: For the pickled cucumber, using a sharp knife or mandoline, slice the cucumber thinly. Combine the cucumber with the remaining ingredients. Cover and refrigerate for 30 mins.
For the wasabi mayonnaise, mix all ingredients in a small bowl.
Combine the ground chicken, soy sauce, egg, breadcrumbs, sesame oil and onion in a large bowl. Shape the mixture into 4 patties.
Cook the patties on a heated oiled grill pan or skillet on medium-high heat for 15 mins or until browned on both sides and cooked through.
Spread the wasabi mayonnaise on the bun bottoms. Sandwich the mizuna, patties and drained pickled cucumber between the bun halves. Serve.

title: thai red curry vegetable pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F.

To make the filling, heat oil in a saucepan over medium-high heat. Cook curry paste and spring onions, stirring, for 3 mins. Add coconut milk. Bring to boil and cook for 5 mins, until reduced and thickened slightly.
Combine stock and cornstarch. Add to pan and stir until thickened. Add vegetables and cilantro. Return to a boil then remove from heat.
Transfer filling to a pie dish and top with puff pastry. Brush with reserved coconut milk and bake for 25-30 mins, until golden brown. Serve.

title: creamy chicken and leek stew
directions: Cook the rice in boiling salted water according to the package instructions.

Heat the butter and oil in a frying pan and saute the leeks for 2 mins. Add the wine and 1/2 cup water. Season, cover and simmer for 5 mins. Add the chicken, mushrooms, cream and 3/4 of the parsley, cover and simmer for 10 mins. Add the lemon zest and juice and season with salt, black pepper and a pinch of sugar.
Drain the rice and spoon into serving bowls. Top with the creamy chicken then garnish with the lemon wedges and remaining parsley.

title: pork chops with rosemary potatoes
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F.
Place pork chops in a glass dish. Mix wine, lemon peel and juice, oil, honey and spices in a small bowl. Pour over pork chops. Cover. Refrigerate 30 mins, turning once, to marinate.
Meanwhile, for the rosemary potatoes, place potatoes in a baking pan. Toss with oil, rosemary and garlic. Season to taste. Bake 40-45 mins, turning once, until golden and crisp.

After potatoes have cooked for 30 mins, melt butter in a large skillet on medium-high heat. Add pork chops and apples, brushing well with marinade. Fry 10-15 mins, turning and basting, until cooked through. Add sage; cook 1-2 mins.
Serve pork chops with drizzled pan juices, apples, potatoes and lemon wedges.

title: slow roasted pork with apple and sage
directions: Heat 2 tsp oil in a large heavy-bottomed saucepan over high heat. Cook pork, turning, until browned all over. Add onions, herbs and wine. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer, covered tightly, for about 1 hour 30 mins, or until pork is cooked to your liking. Transfer to a serving platter and cover to keep warm.
Strain pan juices into a serving vessel. Discard solids. Stir 2 tbsp boiling water into juices and cover to keep warm.
Meanwhile, heat butter and remaining oil in a large frying pan. Cook apple, stirring, for 10 mins, or until tender and golden.
Slice pork. Serve with sauce, apples and onions.

title: asian noodle omlette
directions: Heat half the oil in a medium frying pan over medium heat.
Brush pork with half of the hoisin sauce and cook 8-10 minutes, tuning on all sides, until cooked through. Rest 5 minutes. Slice thinly.

Spray an 8 inch non-stick frying pan with remaining oil. Heat on medium. Reserve 8 oz of noodles and spread one-quarter of remaining noodles over base. Pour 2 beaten eggs over and cook 2-3 minutes until set, the fold in half and cook until eggs are cooked to your liking.
Slide omelette onto a plate and cut in half. Repeat with remaining noodles and eggs.
Serve topped with reserved noodles, beansprouts, pork and cilantro. Drizzle with extra sauce.

title: spicy goulash soup
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan, add meat in batches and sear, turning, for 3-5 mins. Season then remove from pan. Add onion, peppers, mushrooms, bay leaves, and dried parsley and cook for 8-10 mins, stirring. Return meat to pan and add tomato paste. Add flour and cook for 2-3 mins. Season and add hot sauce. Add stock, sugar and potatoes, cover and simmer over low heat for 1 hour 45 mins. Serve sprinkled with fresh parsley.

title: bellini granita
directions: Stir the sugar and 1 cup water in a medium saucepan on medium heat until the sugar is dissolved. Cool to room temperature.
Process the peaches until smooth. Strain through a sieve into a large bowl. Stir in the sugar syrup, wine and juice.
Pour the mixture into a 3-quart dish. Cover, and freeze for 6 hours, scraping the mixture with a fork every hour.
When ready to serve, remove the dish from the freezer. Scrape the granita with a fork; spoon into glasses and serve.

title: chocolate nougat frozen parfait with caramel sauce
directions: Grease a 4 x 8 inch loaf pan. Line base and two long sides with foil or parchment paper, extending above edges of pan.

Process ricotta and 3/4 cups sugar until smooth. Beat 1 1/3 cups of cream in small bowl until soft peaks form. Combine ricotta mixture, candy bar and chocolate in large bowl and fold in whipped cream. Spoon parfait into pan. Cover and freeze overnight or until firm.

Meanwhile, to make caramel sauce, stir remaining sugar and 2/3 cup water in small saucepan over low heat until sugar is dissolved. Boil, uncovered and without stirring, until syrup turns a caramel color.
Remove pan from heat and allow bubbles to subside. Carefully add 2/3 cup of cream and stir over low heat to until combined. Allow to cool.
Remove parfait from pan and cut into slices. Allow to soften slightly before serving with caramel sauce.

title: palm sugar and mango pancakes with fruit salad
directions: Sift flour into a large bowl. Stir in sugar, coconut milk and eggs until smooth. Stir in chopped mango.

Heat a small nonstick skillet on medium heat. Brush with a little butter. For each pancake, pour 2 tbsp batter into pan. Spread to a 5-inch round. Cook for 1-2 mins, until bubbles appear on surface. Flip and cook for 1-2 mins, until golden brown and cooked through. Transfer to a plate. Cover with foil to keep warm. Repeat with remaining butter and batter to make 12 pancakes.
Meanwhile, combine peaches, orange, passionfruit pulp and mint in a medium bowl.
Stack 2 pancakes on each serving plate. Serve with fruit salad and yogurt.

title: fried rice with cashew and shrimp
directions: In a skillet, scramble eggs in oil over medium heat. Remove from skillet. Add peas, carrots, scallion and shrimp. Cook for 1 min, stirring occasionally. Add rice and dressing. Cook over medium-high until heated through, stirring frequently. Stir in cashews and eggs. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Spoon into bowl and garnish with sesame seeds and scallion curls.

title: citrus chicken with bean salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Combine butter, zest and thyme in a small bowl and season to taste. Using fingers, gently separate chicken skin from flesh (don't tear skin).

Spoon 2 heaped tsp butter mixture under skin of each leg. Using hands, rub skin gently to distribute butter mixture evenly. Place chicken in a large roasting pan. Brush with 2 tsp oil. Roast, on top rack, for 25-30 mins or until golden brown and cooked.

Meanwhile, cook broad beans in a medium saucepan of boiling water for 2 mins. Add green beans, cook for 3 mins or until bright green and tender. Drain; refresh under cold running water. Peel broad beans and discard skins.
Combine beans, feta, hazelnuts and garlic in a serving bowl. Drizzle with orange juice and 1 tbsp oil. Serve chicken with bean salad and lemon wedges.

title: iced camomile and honey tea with passionfruit
directions: Place tea bags, honey, lemon juice and passionfruit in a large glass pitcher or jar. Pour in 4 cups boiling water. Let steep until warm. Remove tea bags.
Refrigerate until chilled, about 1 1/2 hours. Serve over ice cubes with lemon slices.

title: southwestern chili
directions: Cook the rice according to the package directions.

Meanwhile, heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add the garlic and onions and cook for 5 mins, stirring often. Add the beef, increase the heat to medium-high and cook until browned, breaking up pieces with a wooden spoon. Spoon off the excess fat. Add the tomatoes, broth, carrots, celery, cumin, oregano and chili powder. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 20 mins, stirring occasionally. Stir in the beans and simmer for 5 mins. Divide among four bowls, top with the rice and garnish with celery leaves.

title: berry and lime cake with whipped coconut cream
directions: Chill unopened can of coconut cream overnight.
Preheat the oven to 325°F. Brush a 9 1/2-inch bundt pan generously with the melted butter.
Finely grate peel from limes. Reserve, separately, 2 tsp for cake and 1 tsp for whipped coconut cream. Juice 1 lime; you will need 2 tbsp juice.

Beat butter and sugar in large bowl with an electric mixer until pale and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, until just combined (mixture may look curdled at this stage). Stir in sifted flours, coconut, buttermilk, frozen berries, and reserved lime peel and juice. Spoon mixture into prepared pan, smoothing surface.
Bake for 50 mins or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan 5 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

Meanwhile, open chilled can of coconut cream. Spoon 1/2 cup of the cream on the surface into a medium bowl (store remaining cream for another use). Add heavy cream and remaining reserved lime peel; beat with electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Spoon half the whipped coconut cream on top of the cake. Decorate with raspberries and coconut flakes. Serve cake with remaining whipped coconut cream.

title: moroccan chicken with buttered couscous
directions: Heat butter and 2 tsp oil in a large frying pan. Toast almonds, stirring, until lightly browned all over. Set aside.

Add remaining oil and cook onion, stirring, until soft. Add spices and cook, stirring, until fragrant. Add roasted chicken wings and drumsticks and toss to coat in spiced onion mixture. Add stock and cook, covered, for 5 mins, or until chicken is heated through.

Meanwhile, for the buttered couscous, bring stock, 1/2 cup water and 1 1/2 tbsp butter to a boil. Pour over couscous, cover and set aside for 3-5 mins. Add remaining butter and fluff couscous with a fork. Season.
To finish, add olives, preserved lemon and almonds to chicken mixture. Serve with buttered couscous and garnish with chopped cilantro.

title: spicy butternut squash soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil over high heat and saute onion, garlic and curry paste for 2-3 mins, until onion is tender. Add squash, potato and carrot and cook, stirring, for 1 min. Add stock and season. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 15-20 mins, or until vegetables are tender. Puree. Let cool slightly then add milk. Reheat gently.
Transfer to serving bowls. Swirl a little heavy cream into each bowl and serve with crusty bread.

title: arancini
directions: Combine the stock and wine in a medium saucepan; bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to low; simmer, covered.
Meanwhile, melt the butter in a medium saucepan on medium heat. Cook the onion and garlic, stirring, until the onion softens. Add the rice and stir until the rice is coated in the butter mixture.

Stir 1/2 cup of the simmering stock mixture into the rice mixture. Cook, stirring, on low heat until the liquid is absorbed. Continue adding the mixture, in 1/2 cup batches, stirring, until the liquid is absorbed after each addition. Total cooking time should be about 35 mins or until the rice is tender. Stir in the cheeses and season to taste. Cover and cool for 30 mins.
Roll rounded tablespoons of the risotto mixture into balls. Press an olive into the center of each ball and roll to enclose. Coat the risotto balls in breadcrumbs.

Heat the oil in a large, deep saucepan on medium-high heat. Deep-fry the risotto balls, in batches, until lightly browned. Drain on paper towels. Accompany with a rich tomato sauce for dipping, if desired.

title: roasted porgy with figs and prosciutto
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Place four of the fish fillets on a chopping board, skin side up, and top with half the sliced prosciutto and figs. Place the 4 remaining fish fillets on top and top with the rest of the prosciutto and figs. Tie each pair of fillets together with fine kitchen string and transfer to a large greased roasting pan.
Drizzle the fish with olive oil, season with salt and freshly ground black pepper and bake for 10-15 mins until the fish is just cooked through.

Meanwhile, heat the butter in a frying pan and fry the shallots over a medium heat for 4-5 mins. Add the spinach and cook gently for a further few mins until the spinach wilts. Add the nutmeg and season to taste. Serve with the baked fish, drizzled with any roasting pan juices.

title: zucchini chocolate cake with pistachio nuts
directions: Blend 1 cup of the butter with the sugar and vanilla extract. Next, beat the eggs into the mixture one at a time. Sift the flour and 3/4 cup of the cocoa powder together with the baking soda and a pinch of salt. Next, fold in a little of the flour, then a little of the yoghurt to the mixture, and repeat until the ingredients are used up. Finally, fold in the grated zucchini.

Grease a 9 1/2 inch springform cake pan, and pour in the mixture. Bake in a preheated oven at 350°F for 35-45 mins. Check that the cake is baked by inserting a skewer into the middle of the cake: it should come out clean. Remove the cake from the tin and allow to cool on a wire rack.

Toast the pistachio nuts in a pan then remove them from the pan. When they are cool, roughly chop them and set to one side. To make the frosting, beat the rest of the butter and the icing sugar together, then stir in the rest of the cocoa powder. When the cake has cooled, slice it in half horizontally taking care to ensure that the slices are even and level. Spread half the frosting on the top of the bottom half of the cake, then sprinkle with half the pistachios. Place the second half on top, and cover with frosting, sprinkling with pistachios to finish. Chill the cake in the refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: falafels in baguette batons
directions: Puree the chickpeas, onion and garlic. Mix with the egg yolks, bread crumbs, chopped arugula, tomato paste and flour and season to taste. Heat the oil in a deep pan. With moistened hands, form 8 falafel balls. Carefully put the falafel in the hot oil and deep fry for 4-5 minutes until browned. Drain on paper towels.

Mix the mayonnaise and the pesto together. Cut the baguettes in half horizontally and brush both halves with mayonnaise. Place the arugula on the bottom half of each baguette, then add the falafel, peppers and onions and top with the other half of the baguette.

title: vodka citron cocktail
directions: Fill a cocktail shaker with ice and top with vodka, Cointreau and lemon juice. Replace the lid and shake well for 15 secs.
Pour the cocktail into glasses. Squeeze a strip of orange zest over each glass, rub the skin around the rim of the glass, and drop it into cocktail. Serve immediately and enjoy.

title: turkey with brown rice salad
directions: Cook rice in boiling salted water according to package directions. Drain, rinse under cold water and let cool.
Heat oil in a frying pan, season turkey and saute for 6-8 mins, turning, until cooked through. Set aside and allow to rest.
Arrange rice and mixed greens on serving plates. Slice turkey and arrange on top. Drizzle with dressing. Season.

title: string bean fries
directions: Cook the beans in boiling salted water for 5 mins. Drain them and rinse them in cold water.

Put the flour and breadcrumbs on separate plates and beat the eggs. Dip the beans one at a time, first in the flour, then in the egg and finally in the breadcrumbs. Fry them in batches in hot oil for about 2 mins until golden brown. Lift them out with a slotted spoon and drain them on paper towels.

title: chocolate spelt waffles with caramel sauce
directions: For the caramel sauce, bring caramels and cream to a boil, stirring. Stir until caramels melt then simmer for 15 mins, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and let cool, stirring occasionally.

Meanwhile, whisk together butter, sugar, vanilla extract and a pinch of salt until creamy. Beat in eggs and 1/4 cup flour. Mix baking powder and remaining flour together then stir into batter, along with milk and yogurt.
Heat a heart-shaped waffle iron and brush with a little oil. Add 2 tbsp batter and cook for 2 mins, or until golden. Transfer to a wire rack. Repeat with remaining batter.
Dip waffles in melted chocolate. Lay on parchment paper and allow to dry. Serve with caramel sauce.

title: apricot parfait
directions: Bring apricots and 1/2 cup water to a boil. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 mins, or until soft. Let cool then process until smooth.

Combine custard, cookie crumbles and orange zest. Distribute 1/2 between 4 - 8 oz serving glasses. Top with 1/2 apricot puree and 1/2 strawberries. Repeat layers. Top with sliced almonds. Cover with plastic wrap and chill for 10 mins.

title: grilled steak quesadillas
directions: Preheat the grill on medium heat.
Brush steak with 1 tbsp of the oil. Grill 2-3 mins each side. Transfer to a plate. Cover loosely; let stand 5 mins. Slice thinly.
Meanwhile, spread 4 of the tortillas with guacamole; top evenly with cheese, onion and cilantro. Top with steak and a second tortilla.
Heat remaining 1 tbsp oil in a large skillet on high heat. Cook each quesadilla 1-2 mins each side, until golden.
Top with sour cream and additional cilantro. Serve with salsa.

title: herb and tomato fish bundles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Make 4 (8 inch) squares of parchment paper or foil.

Distribute fish, tomatoes, capers, thyme, vinegar and oil between squares of parchment. Gather corners together above fish and twist to enclose securely. Place on a baking tray and roast for 15 mins. Let rest for 5 mins before serving.

title: smoked salmon and mascarpone crepe cake with pea salad
directions: Line bottom and side of a deep 9-inch round cake pan with plastic wrap.
Place flour in a large bowl. Gradually whisk in combined eggs, oil and milk. Strain batter into large measuring cup; cover. Let stand for 30 mins.

Heat oiled 9-inch nonstick skillet on low heat. Pour about 1/4 cup batter into pan, tilting pan so batter coats bottom evenly. Cook crepe, loosening around edge with spatula, until lightly browned. Turn; brown other side. Remove from pan. Repeat with remaining batter to make 8 crepes.

Combine mascarpone, horseradish, capers, tarragon and lemon peel in medium bowl; stir to combine. Place a crepe in prepared pan. Spread with about 1/3 cup of the mascarpone mixture. Cover with slices of salmon. Continue layering with remaining crepes, mascarpone mixture and salmon, finishing with crepe layer. Cover; refrigerate for 3 hours, or until firm.

Meanwhile, for the pea salad, boil, steam or microwave sugar snap and snow peas, separately, until just tender; drain. Rinse under cold water; drain. Place in large bowl with remaining ingredients; toss gently to combine.
Cut crepe cake into 8 wedges. Serve with pea salad.

title: spiced eggplant and kidney beans
directions: Heat olive oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Saute onion and garlic 2-3 mins, until softened. Add eggplant, zucchini, chili and paprika. Cook, stirring, 5-6 mins.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, stock, tomato paste and sugar. Bring to a boil on high, reduce heat to low and simmer 10-15 mins, until sauce thickens.
In a bowl, combine yogurt, lemon juice, mint and a few drops Tabasco. Season to taste.
Stir cilantro leaves into the eggplant, season to taste. Serve with rice and yogurt sauce.

title: vegetable ramen
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick frying pan over high heat, add egg and cook, stirring, for 2-3 mins, or until lightly browned and cooked. Set aside and let cool.
Toss with remaining ingredients.

title: kale and broccoli slaw
directions: In a blender, puree dressing with avocado and oregano.
In a large bowl, combine kale, broccoli slaw, pepper, onion, cranberries and almonds. Add dressing and toss to combine. Season.

title: chocolate hazelnut tarts
directions: Bake the puff pastry shells according to the package directions. Cool completely on a wire rack.
Place the cream, chocolate, Nutella and butter in a medium saucepan on medium heat. Cook and stir until smooth. Pour mixture into pastry shells. Refrigerate for at least 40 mins until firm.
Dust lightly with cocoa powder. Garnish with white chocolate shapes.

title: onion and fennel fish parcels
directions: Heat the oil in a medium saucepan over medium-low heat. Add the onion and fennel and saute until soft. Add the butter and garlic and stir over medium heat for 5 mins or until creamy. Season to taste.

Preheat the oven to 375°F. To assemble, spread the onion mixture in the center of 4 pieces of parchment paper (16 x 12 inch). Top with the fish and season. Sprinkle with fennel seeds, then top with the lemon slices. Close the paper around the fish and fold it under. Transfer the parcels to a baking sheet. Bake for 10-15 mins or until the fish is just cooked. Open the paper and sprinkle with the reserved fennel tops. Serve with the mixed greens.

title: apricot eggnog cheesecake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Whip the egg whites to stiff peaks. Gradually add the sugar, then the vanilla extract and a pinch of salt, beating. Next, stir in the egg yolks, one by one. Sift the cornstarch with the flour then add to the mixture. Finally, fold in the almond flour. Line the bottom of 10 inch springform cake pan with parchment paper, and pour in the cake mixture, smoothing the surface with a flat knife. Bake for 20-25 mins. Remove from the oven and allow the cake to rest in the pan on a wire rack until cool.

When the cake is almost cool, start the topping. Whip the cream until it is firm. Meanwhile, beat the cream cheese, then stir in the apricots and then fold in the cream, taking care to ensure the mixture stays light and airy. Spoon the mixture on top of the cooled cake base and smooth the top with a flat knife. Put the cake in the refrigerator to cool for about an hour.

Next, soak the gelatin in a few tablespoons of cold water until hydrated. If using sheet gelatin, gently squeeze any excess water from the sheets. Place the gelatin in a small saucepan with 2 tablespoons of eggnog and melt it over a low heat, stirring, until the gelatin has completely dissolved, then stir in the rest of the eggnog. Pour the eggnog over the top of the cream cheese and refrigerate for an additional 2 hours.

Remove the cake from the pan and transfer to a serving plate to decorate. Sprinkle the sides with a little of the grated chocolate, then sprinkle chocolate shapes on top of the cake (you can use stencils or a pastry cutter for this), and serve.

title: caramel almond bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease and line an 8x12 inch rimmed baking pan with parchment paper, extending paper 2 inches over long sides.

In a stand mixer, beat butter and powdered sugar together until pale and creamy. Stir in egg yolks then flour. Mix until just combined. Transfer to prepared pan and press into base. Bake for 10-12 mins, until light golden brown.
Reduce oven to 325°F.

In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, butter and honey. Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves. Simmer for 3-5 mins, until mixture is golden then stir in almonds. Spread almond mixture evenly over cookie base. Bake for 15-20 mins, until topping is golden brown. Let cool in pan for 5 mins. Cut into squares while still warm then let cool completely.

title: indonesian fried rice
directions: Heat oil in wok or large skillet on high heat. Stir-fry onion, garlic and chili pepper until onion softens. Add tofu; stir-fry until tofu browns lightly.
Add cooked rice, soy sauce and green onions; stir-fry until heated through and well combined.
Meanwhile, heat oiled medium skillet on medium skillet. Cook eggs, in batches, on both sides, until just cooked.
Divide fried rice among serving bowls; top each with a fried egg.

title: buttermilk pancakes with maple berries
directions: Sift flour and baking soda into a large bowl. Stir in sugar. Make a well in the center of the flour mixture. Gradually whisk in combined buttermilk and egg until smooth.

Melt 1 tsp butter in large skillet on medium heat. Pour 1/4 cupfuls of batter into pan in batches. Cook 2 mins until bubbles appear on surface and bottom is golden. Turn and cook further 1-2 mins, until cooked through.
Transfer to a plate and cover to keep warm. Repeat with remaining batter, melting more butter in pan as needed.
For the maple berries, combine all ingredients in medium saucepan on medium heat. Bring to a simmer. Cook gently 3-4 mins, stirring occasionally, until mixture has slightly thickened.
Serve pancakes with warm berries and a dollop of yogurt.

title: tiramisu cake with berries
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F. Grease a 9 inch square cake pan and line base with parchment paper.

In a medium saucepan, combine butter, 2 tsp instant coffee powder, 3/4 cup hot water, chocolate and 1 cup sugar. Stir over low heat until chocolate melts. Transfer to a large bowl and let cool for 5 mins.

In 2 batches, whisk in flour and 2 tbsp cocoa powder. Whisk in egg and vanilla extract. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 40 mins. Let cake cool in pan for 5 mins then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.

Meanwhile, place 1 2/3 cups water in a medium saucepan. Add remaining sugar and coffee. Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil. Boil, without stirring, for 5 mins. Remove from heat and stir in marsala. Let cool. Reserve 1/3 cup coffee syrup.
Split cake in 1/2 horizontally. Place halves, crust-side up, on a tray. Brush with remaining coffee syrup. Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours, or overnight.
Cut each cake 1/2 into 8 equal pieces. Whisk together mascarpone, cream and reserved coffee syrup in a medium bowl until mixture thickens slightly.

Arrange 8 serving dishes on a flat work surface. Place a piece of cake in each dish. Distribute 1/2 the mascarpone mixture over top. Repeat layers, using remaining cake and mascarpone mixture. Top with raspberries and dust with remaining cocoa powder.

title: prosecco and elderberry cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Line the bottom of a 10 inch diameter springform pan with parchment paper. Beat the egg whites, 3 tbsp cold water and a pinch of salt until they form stiff peaks, gradually adding the sugar and 1 tsp vanilla extract. Beat in the egg yolks one at a time. Sift in the flour, cornstarch and baking powder and fold in. Spoon into the pan and smooth out. Bake for 25-30 mins, until a skewer comes out clean. Allow to cool.

Turn out of the pan and cut in half horizontally by inserting a knife into the center and rotating the cake around it. Place the bottom cake on a cake plate and place a cake ring around it. Spread with the jam.

Squeeze out the gelatin and dissolve in a saucepan over a low heat, or add 3 tbsp of water to the powdered gelatin. Stir in the elderflower syrup, then the prosecco. Chill for 25 mins, or until the mixture begins to set. Whip 1 3/4 cups of cream until it forms stiff peaks. Stir the prosecco mixture, then fold in half the cream. Chill for 5 mins, then fold in the remaining cream. Spread over the bottom cake layer , then press the second cake lightly on top. Chill overnight.

Whip the remaining cream and 1 tsp vanilla extract until it forms stiff peaks. Remove the cake ring and spread two-thirds of the cream over the top and sides of the cake. Press the pistachios around the edge. Spoon the remaining cream into a piping bag fitted with a medium star nozzle and pipe rosettes of cream over the top of the cake. Decorate with sugar flowers.

title: lemon trifle
directions: Arrange fruit cake in a large glass serving bowl. Drizzle custard over top. Sprinkle 2/3 of raspberries over custard. Whip cream to soft peaks then fold into lemon curd. Pour over raspberries. Cover with plastic wrap and chill for 1 hour.
Sprinkle remaining raspberries and pistachios over trifle. Garnish with chocolate curls.

title: spiced bhaji (oven-roasted chickpeas)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line a baking tray with parchment paper.

Cook chickpeas in boiling salted water for 30 mins, or until tender. Drain. Let cool. Add tandoori paste and toss to coat. Add nibble mix, chickpea flour, garam masala and oil. Toss to combine. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 25 mins, or until golden. Let cool on tray. Add noodles and toss to combine. Serve.

title: fish and sweet potato chips
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Line a baking pan with parchment paper. Cut sweet potatoes in half lengthwise then cut each half into 1/4 inch-thick slices. Cut slices into 1/4 inch-thick chips. Toss in 1 tbsp of the oil.
Place in a single layer on the prepared pan. Roast for 15 mins, or until golden and cooked through.

Meanwhile, mix spices, salt, sesame seeds and breadcrumbs in wide shallow bowl. Place flour and egg in 2 other shallow bowls. Coat fish all over in flour, shaking off any excess. Dip in egg, then dip in breadcrumb mixture, turning until fish is covered all over.
Heat remaining 1 tbsp oil in a large, ovenproof skillet on medium heat. Cook fish until browned on both sides. Transfer to oven and bake until just cooked through.
Meanwhile, for the lime and coriander yogurt, mix all ingredients in small bowl. Serve fish and chips with yogurt and lime wedges, if desired.

title: green tea orzo with roasted peppers
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Rub the peppers with 1 tbsp oil and place on a baking tray. Roast for 25-30 mins until the skins are charred and blistered. Place the hot peppers in a plastic bag and set aside for 15 mins until cool enough to handle. Remove the skin and cut into strips, discarding the seeds and pith.

Meanwhile, mix the green tea with 2 1/2 cups hot water. Heat the remaining oil in a wide pan and saute the onion over medium heat for 5 mins. Add the orzo and saute for 1 min then add the white wine. Simmer for 1 min then add the green tea and season. Simmer for about 15 mins until the pasta is tender then add the lemon juice and adjust the seasoning. Divide the pasta between 4 serving bowls and top with the warm peppers. Garnish with thyme and lemon zest.

title: fruity oatmeal
directions: Place oats and milk in a medium saucepan on medium heat. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer, stirring, for 3-4 mins until thick and creamy.
Spoon into serving bowls. Top with fruit and drizzle with honey.

title: rum crème caramel
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F. Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup water in a saucepan over medium heat, stirring, until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil and cook for 10-12 mins, undisturbed, until a light caramel color. Carefully distribute between six 4.25oz ramekins, swirling to cover base.

Whisk together eggs, remaining sugar and rum extract until combined. Bring evaporated milk and milk to a boil then whisk into eggs. Strain then distribute between prepared ramekins. Transfer ramekins to a baking dish. Add enough boiling water to come halfway up sides of ramekins. Bake for 25-30 mins, until just set. Remove from baking dish and chill overnight.
To serve, turn out onto a serving plate.

title: banana and pecan loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and line a 6x10 inch loaf pan. For the batter, sift flour and cinnamon into a large bowl. Add all remaining ingredients except for the honey and butter, mixing until just combined. Pour into prepared pan and level the top. Bake for 45-50 mins. Remove from oven and cover with foil to prevent further browning. Bake for 45-50 more mins, until golden and a skewer comes out clean. Cool in pan for 5 mins then turn out onto a wire rack to cool completely. Serve with butter and honey.

title: bacon, cheese and chili muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Oil 3 - 6-cup muffin pans.
Place a medium frying pan over medium-high heat. Cook bacon, stirring, until crisp then drain on paper towels.

In a food processor, combine flour, butter, paprika and chili flakes and process until mixture resembles breadcrumbs. Transfer to a medium bowl and stir in bacon, cheese and corn. Whisk together egg and buttermilk then add to dry ingredients and mix until combined. Spoon 1/4 cup batter into each muffin recess and bake for 20 mins. Turn muffins out onto a wire rack. Serve warm.

title: rocky road brownie
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Grease a foil lined 8 inch square baking pan, with foil extending at 2 opposite sides for handles.
Place butter and milk chocolate in a medium saucepan on low heat. Cook and stir for 5 mins or until melted and smooth. Remove from heat. Stir in sugar, then egg; mix well.
Sift flour and cocoa powder over chocolate mixture. Stir until combined. Stir in peanuts, coconut and 4 oz of the semi-sweet chocolate. Pour mixture into prepared pan; smooth surface with a spatula.

Bake for 45 mins or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out with crumbs attached. Cover top of brownie with marshmallows, cut-side down. Return to oven for 30 seconds or until marshmallows soften. Cool in pan.

Place remaining 2 oz semi-sweet chocolate in a heatproof bowl over a saucepan of simmering water (don't let base of bowl touch the water). Stir until melted and smooth. Transfer brownie to a board. Cut into 20 pieces. Drizzle melted chocolate over brownie pieces in a crisscross pattern. Let stand until chocolate sets.

title: chocolate rum truffles
directions: Place chocolate in a large heatproof bowl. Place cream and butter in a small saucepan on medium heat. Stir until almost boiling. Remove from heat and pour over chocolate. Let stand 2 mins, then stir until smooth. Add rum. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Line a large tray with parchment paper. Place cocoa powder, almonds and coconut in separate shallow bowls.

Using a melon baller or hands, shape heaping teaspoons of mixture into balls. Roll in cocoa or other toppings to coat well. Place on tray. Refrigerate 20 mins. Serve with drinks or package as a gift in a box tied with ribbon.

title: zucchini kebabs and lamb köfte
directions: Soak the wooden skewers for at least 1 hour. Place a piece of Halloumi at one end of a courgette slice, roll up and thread onto a metal skewer. Repeat, so that each metal skewer has 3 Halloumi rolls on it.
Wrap each apricot in a slice of bacon. Set aside.

Place the onion in a large bowl with the garlic, chili, honey, nutmeg, cinnamon and mince. Knead until smooth. Season with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Shape into 16 wide and slightly flattened sausage shapes. Thread onto the wooden skewers with a bacon wrapped apricot.
Grill or barbecue the skewers for 10-15 mins, turning occasionally, until cooked through.

title: thai beef rice paper rolls
directions: Pan-fry the steak in hot skillet until seared on both sides and cooked to desired doneness. Transfer the steak to a plate; cool slightly. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Cut the chilled steak into wafer-thin slices.

Place the vermicelli in a heatproof bowl and cover with boiling water. Let stand for 5 mins, stirring to separate strands. Drain the vermicelli in a strainer. Rinse under cold water, then drain again, pressing down firmly to remove excess liquid.

Dip a rice paper wrapper briefly in a dish of warm water to soften. Place the wrapper on a cutting board. Spread about 1 tsp sweet chili sauce on one end of wrapper. Layer a little lettuce, vermicelli and sliced steak over sauce. Rolling up from filled end, folding in the sides. When the wrapper is half rolled up, place 1-2 cilantro leaves on top and continue rolling up to enclose filling and cilantro leaves and form a neat roll. Repeat with remaining wrappers and filling ingredients.
Serve rolls with additional sweet chili sauce.

title: almond and butter cookies
directions: Heat butter in a small saucepan until light brown, then pour it into a bowl and leave to cool.

Mix the flour, baking powder and 1 pinch of salt. In another bowl whisk the eggs, white sugar, cinnamon, chopped almonds and a pinch of salt until creamy. Fold in the brown sugar and 'brown butter' and continue beating the mixture for 3 mins. Add the flour mixture and stir 3.5 oz of chopped chocolate. Chill for 30 mins.

Preheat the oven to 350°F. With a small ice cream scoop, distribute approximately 25 mounds of dough on 2 baking sheets lined with parchment paper. Bake for 12-14 mins each and leave the cookies on the baking sheets to cool.

Cut the remaining almonds in half lengthwise. Melt the remaining 5.25 oz chocolate over a bain marie and leave it to cool. Spread about 1 tsp of chocolate on each cookie and arrange the almond halves on the chocolate. Set the cookies aside to dry in a cool place.

title: coleslaw
directions: Whisk together mayonnaise and white wine vinegar in a large serving bowl.
Add white cabbage, red cabbage, carrot and onions to bowl and toss gently to combine.

title: chunky watermelon salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl, tossing to mix well. Serve.

title: curried beef and couscous
directions: Bring 1 1/4 cups water to a boil. Remove from heat and add couscous. Cover and let stand for 5 mins, or until water is completely absorbed.
Meanwhile, combine beef, ginger, garlic, cardamom, cumin and curry paste in a bowl. Heat oil in a large saucepan. Working in batches, cook beef until tender. Remove from pan.
Add onions to pan and cook, stirring, until softened. Return beef to pan along with couscous, tomatoes, yogurt, crumbled bouillon cube and 1/3 cup water. Stir over medium heat until hot.
Serve sprinkled with fresh cilantro.

title: cabbage tart tatin
directions: Preheat oven 425°F.

Melt butter in a 10 inch ovenproof frying pan. Saute shallots for 3-4 mins, until golden. Add sugar and vinegar, stirring to dissolve. Season to taste. Arrange cabbage in frying pan, covering base evenly. Cook over low heat for 15-20 mins, without stirring, until underside begins to caramelize and excess liquid evaporates. Let cool slightly.

Overlap pastry sheets slightly and trim into a circle. Cover pan with pastry, tucking edges underneath cabbage. Prick with a fork and bake for 20-25 mins, until pastry is puffed and golden brown. Turn out onto a cutting board and cut into wedges. Serve immediately.

title: giant spinach and sausage ravioli
directions: Place the flour in a large bowl and create a well in the center. Add 3 eggs and 2 tbsp of oil into the well. Bring together with your fingertips or a fork. Once it resembles breadcrumbs, place dough on a floured wooden board or work surface. Knead well, for 8-10 minutes, adding a little water if necessary 1-2 tbsp at a time. Keep the dough moving and turning, until it is silky and smooth, not rough and floury. Return to the bowl and cover with a damp clean tea towel to rest at room temperature.
Meanwhile, to make the filling, place the spinach in a pot of boiling water, cover, and simmer for 5 minutes. Drain. Allow to cool and squeeze out the excess water.
Soak the bread roll in cold water. Squeeze out the excess water and chop finely.
Place the pork, sausage, parsley, bread, 2 eggs, and the spinach into a bowl. Season with salt and freshly ground black pepper and mix to combine.
Split the pasta dough in half and run through a pasta machine so you have two thin strips approximately 6 inch x 2 1/2 feet.

Place the pasta strips on a work surface dusted with flour. Place the meat mixture along one half of each strip leaving a 1/2 inch border (brush the border with a little water). Fold over and seal. Cut each strip into 8 squares and press the cut edges firmly to seal. Place onto a floured baking sheet.
Heat 2 tbsp oil in a large pan and saute the onion slices until golden brown. Set aside.
Bring the stock to a boil, add the ravioli, and cook for 8-10 minutes until cooked through. Divide the ravioli and broth between four bowls. Garnish with the onions and chives.

title: grilled potato, plums, bacon and blue cheese raclette
directions: Cook potatoes for 20 mins in boiling water. Drain and set aside to cool. Break up potatoes into small pieces.
Cook bacon on the grill plate of the raclette until crispy. Arrange potatoes, diced plums and bacon in the raclette pan. Top with cheese slices and grill for 5 mins. Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: tamarind honey shrimp with pineapple
directions: Heat the oil in a wok on high heat. Stir-fry the shrimp, garlic, chili pepper, red pepper and snow peas until the shrimp change color.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir-fry until heated through.

title: strawberry gratin
directions: Preheat broiler. Lightly grease 4 individual gratin dishes.
Combine strawberries and vodka then distribute between prepared dishes. Top with cream and sprinkle with sugar and almonds. Broil for 2-3 min, until sugar is caramelized. Serve immediately.

title: duck and lentil salad
directions: Cook lentils according to package instructions. Drain.

Heat 1 tbsp oil in saucepan, add chopped onion and carrots and cook, stirring, for 2-3 mins. Add lentils then allow to cool slightly. Add 1/2 sliced onion along with apples, vinegar, thyme, 3 tbsp olive oil and honey. Season. Add duck breast and walnuts. Divide between 4 plates and garnish with extra thyme and remaining sliced onion.

title: chili pork salad
directions: Lightly coat a large frying pan with oil and place over medium heat. Add eggs and tilt pan to cover base. Cook for 1 min, or until set underneath. Flip over and cook for 1 min, or until golden and set. Transfer to a cutting board, roll into a log and slice thinly.
Lightly coat pork with oil. Cook for 2 mins per side then transfer to a plate. Cover with foil and let rest for 5 mins. Slice.

Whisk chili sauce, fish sauce, lime juice and garlic together. Combine mixed greens, corn, tomatoes, sprouts, cilantro, onions, pork and egg in a large bowl. Drizzle dressing over salad and toss to combine. Spoon into serving bowls. Serve immediately.

title: chocolate cake with fudge frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease a deep 11x13 inch baking dish and line base with baking paper.

Combine sugar, butter, cocoa powder, baking soda and 2 cups water in a medium saucepan. Stir over high heat, without boiling, until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 5 mins. Transfer to a large bowl and let cool to room temperature.
Once cool, beat in flour and eggs until smooth. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 50 mins. Let cool in pan for 10 mins then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.

Meanwhile, for the fudge frosting, stir butter, 1/3 cup water and sugar in a small saucepan over low heat, without boiling, until sugar dissolves. Sift powdered sugar and cocoa powder into a small bowl. Gradually stir in hot butter mixture. Cover and chill for 20 mins, or until thickened. Beat with a wooden spoon until spreadable.
Spread frosting over cooled cake.

title: sesame shrimp toast
directions: Cut the crusts from the bread. In a food processor, combine the shrimp, spring onions, ginger, egg white, cornstarch, soy sauce, and pepper; process until smooth.

Spread the shrimp mixture evenly onto one side of each bread slice. Cut each slice into 4 triangles. Place the sesame seeds on a plate and press the bread, shrimp-side down, in to the sesame seeds to coat.

Heat the oil in a wok or large heavy-based saucepan over moderately high heat (oil is ready when a cube of bread crisps quickly in 30 secs without absorbing oil). Deep-fry the toast in batches, prawn-side down for 1 min. Turn and cook for 30 secs more, or until golden brown. Drain on kitchen paper and serve immediately.

title: sweet spiced pork and noodles
directions: Bring a large saucepan of water to a boil. Add pork; boil for 3 mins. Drain pork. Add soy sauces, sherry, sugar, star anise, cinnamon, ginger and garlic to pan; cook and stir on medium heat for 1 min or until combined.
Return pork to pan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours or until pork is very tender and sauce is syrupy. (You may need to stir occasionally as sauce thickens.)
Meanwhile, soak noodles in boiling water in a medium heatproof bowl for 3 mins. Stir to separate strands. Drain.
Place carrot and snow peas in another heatproof bowl. Cover with boiling water; let stand for 3 mins. Drain. Toss vegetables with bean sprouts and onion.
To serve, place noodles in large shallow serving bowls. Top with pork and drizzle with sauce. Pile vegetables over pork and serve while hot.

title: lamb with eggplant and tomato salad
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F.
Preheat a grill plate or grill. Coat eggplant with oil then grill until tender.
Combine onion, vinegar, sugar, garlic, butter and 2 tbsp oil in a large shallow baking dish. Roast for 10 mins. Remove from oven and stir in parsley. Let cool for 5 mins.
Meanwhile, drizzle tomatoes with remaining oil then roast for 10 mins.
Rub lamb with sumac. Grill until cooked to your liking. Cover lamb and let rest for 5 mins. Slice thickly.
Combine arugula, raisins and onion mixture in a large bowl and toss gently to combine. Distribute eggplant between serving plates. Top with arugula mixture, lamb and tomatoes.

title: baked chicken legs with mediterranean vegetables
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. In a small bowl, mix the paprika with 3 tbsp olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Place the chicken and potatoes in a large bowl, drizzle with the paprika oil and mix well. Transfer to a large casserole dish. Bake for 15 mins.

Meanwhile, place the bell peppers, zucchini, garlic and thyme leaves in a bowl. Drizzle over 2 tbsp olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Mix well. Add to the casserole and bake for 30 mins. Add the tomatoes and bake for 15 mins until the vegetables are tender and the chicken is cooked through.
In a large salad bowl, mix the shallot, vinegar and mustard. Season with salt and pepper. Gradually whisk in the remaining 3 tbsp olive oil. Add the arugula and toss to coat.
Garnish the chicken and vegetables with the extra thyme. Serve with the arugula salad.

title: cherry jam and ricotta with scones
directions: Place cherries, sugar and juice in a large heavy-based saucepan over moderate heat. Cook and stir until sugar dissolves. Increase heat to moderately high. Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 25 minutes or until jam reaches setting point. Remove pan from heat. Transfer hot jam to hot sterilized jars. Seal while hot. Cool.
Combine ricotta, powdered sugar and cinnamon in a medium bowl.
Spread split scones with ricotta mixture and top with cherry jam. Serve.

title: barley and kale soup
directions: Blanch the kale in boiling water for 4-5 mins. Drain well and let cool. Coarsely chop the kale. Heat the oil in a saucepan and saute the onion and garlic. Add the kale and saute briefly. Season well and add the stock.

Add the pearl barley and raisins and cook on a low heat at a simmer for 20-30 minutes. Meanwhile, dry roast the pine nuts in a frying pan until golden brown. Shortly before the end of cooking add the pine nuts to the kale mixture and stir. Add the curry powder and cumin and season to taste. Serve in bowls, garnished with a dollop of sour cream.

title: chicken stew
directions: Mix the flour and dried thyme in a bowl and coat the chicken with the mixture. Heat 2 tbsp of oil in a large pot and fry the chicken briefly, turning as necessary until browned on all sides. Remove chicken and add 2 more tbsp of oil to the pot and saute the potatoes for 4-5 mins. Add the cabbage and garlic and saute for 2 minutes. Pour in the stock, bring to a boil, and simmer for about 5 minutes. Add the peas, broccoli, spring onions and chicken. Cover, and simmer for 25 mins.

Toast pine nuts in a small dry pan, until they're golden brown. Puree the pine nuts, basil, tarragon and 6 tbsp olive oil in a food processor and stir the pesto into the stew. Serve garnished with basil.

title: marshmallow and chocolate stacks
directions: Place 2 squares of chocolate on one graham cracker. Spear 2 marshmallows on a clean stick and toast over a campfire until golden, or done to your liking (remember they burn very easily). Put the marshmallows on top of the chocolate (still on the stick), then place the top graham cracker in place, pressing gently, then slide out the stick. Wait a second for the heat to slightly melt the chocolate. Repeat with the remaining graham crackers, chocolate and marshmallows.

If you don't have a campfire, you can toast the marshmallows carefully over a gas flame in the kitchen, or, heat them on a plate for about 20 seconds in a microwave, until they are puffed and gooey. Another option is to put the graham crackers on a microwave-safe plate and top with chocolate then marshmallows. Microwave for about 3 mins, or until the marshmallows are puffed and the chocolate begins to melt. Top with more graham crackers, cool slightly, then serve.

title: butter chicken curry
directions: Combine curry paste and yogurt. Add chicken and stir to coat. Cover with plastic wrap and chill for 2 hours to marinate.
Heat oil and butter in a large, deep frying pan over medium heat. Cook onion for 5 mins, or until soft. Add tomatoes and cook for 2-3 mins, or until mixture boils.

Add chicken mixture, stirring until combined. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer for 15 mins. Add green beans. Simmer for 8 mins, or until chicken is cooked through. Remove from heat then stir in spinach and cilantro.
Spoon rice onto serving plates. Top with curry then garnish with cashews and cilantro sprigs. Serve with poppadums.

title: cheese and onion dumplings with cabbage and bacon
directions: Combine bread and lukewarm milk. Set aside for 30 mins, to soak.
Meanwhile, heat butter in a large frying pan. Cook onion, stirring, for 2 mins. Set aside to cool.
Dust soaked bread with flour. Add eggs, cottage cheese, chives, cooked onion and cheese and mix until combined. Season. Set aside for 30 mins.
Heat oil in a frying pan. Cook bacon, stirring occasionally, for 2-3 mins. Set aside.
Form bread mixture into dumplings. Cook in salted boiling water for 10 mins. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.

Meanwhile, blanch cabbage in salted boiling water for 3-4 mins. Drain then add to pan along with bacon. Return to heat and cook, stirring, for 1 min. Serve with dumplings. Garnish with reserved cheese and chives.

title: chili calamari with bean and tomato salad
directions: To make bean salad, combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Season to taste. Toss gently.
To make calamari, combine calamari, sambal oelek and garlic In a medium bowl and toss well to coat.
In a large pan, heat oil on high. Cook calamari 3-5 minutes, turning, until opaque and cooked through.
Serve with calamari with the bean salad and lemon wedges.

title: tuna and chickpea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a serving bowl. Season to taste and toss to combine.

title: roasted tomato, caramelized onion and olive quiche
directions: For the pastry, sift flour into a large bowl. Rub in butter using fingertips, until mixture resembles breadcrumbs.
Add yolk and 1 tbsp ice-cold water to make a firm but pliable dough. Knead lightly. Wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate 30 mins.

Grease 9-inch round tart pan with removable bottom. Roll pastry between sheets of parchment paper until large enough to line prepared pan. Press pastry into bottom and side of pan; trim edge. Prick bottom with fork. Cover; refrigerate for 15 mins.
Preheat the oven to 400°F. Place tart pan on baking pan. Line pastry with parchment paper and fill with baking beans. Bake for 10 mins; remove paper and beans. Bake for 5 mins; cool.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°F. For the filling, place tomatoes, cut-side up, in a baking pan. Roast 20-25 mins. Cool.

Meanwhile, melt butter in a medium skillet on medium heat. Saute onion and garlic for 2-3 mins, until tender and lightly browned. Stir in vinegar and sugar. Cook, stirring, for 10-15 mins, until caramelized. Cool.
Whisk eggs, cream and milk in a medium bowl. Season to taste.
Arrange tomatoes, onion mixture, olives and anchovies in crust. Pour egg mixture over the top.
Bake for 35-40 mins, until set. Serve quiche in wedges,

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Brush an 8-inch square cake pan with melted butter. Line base and sides with parchment.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, and baking powder in a bowl. Crack eggs into a bowl and whisk lightly. Add eggs to flour along with oil, walnuts, bananas and pineapple. Stir until combined.
Pour into prepared pan and smooth surface. Bake for 1 hour, or until a skewer comes out clean. Invert onto a wire rack and allow to cool.
With an electric mixer, beat cream cheese until pale. Gradually beat in confectioners' sugar until light and fluffy. Spread over cake.

title: lamb and chickpea patties
directions: Combine ground lamb, breadcrumbs, onion, curry paste, egg white, cilantro and chickpeas in a large bowl. Shape into 12 patties. Place on a plate, cover with plastic wrap and chill for 15 mins.
Place a lightly oiled grill plate over medium heat. Grill patties for 5 mins per side, or until browned and cooked through. Transfer to a heatproof plate and cover with foil to keep warm.
Meanwhile, lightly coat both sides of pita bread with oil. Grill for 1-2 mins, or until lightly browned.
Place pita bread on plates. Top with lettuce, patties and chutney. Serve with lemon wedges.

title: corn and polenta muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease a 12-cup muffin pan. Sift flour and baking powder together. Add polenta, tomatoes and onion. Whisk together sour cream, corn, eggs and oil then add to dry ingredients. Season and mix until just combined. Distribute between muffin wells and bake for 15-20 mins, until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: almond and apricot roulade
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and line a 9x13 inch jelly roll pan with parchment paper. Dust with flour.

Whisk eggs and sugar over a double boiler until thick enough to leave a trail on surface when whisk is lifted. Remove from heat and whisk until cool. Sift flour over batter then fold in. Add 1 tbsp hot water and almond extract. Transfer to prepared pan and spread out evenly. Sprinkle with almonds and bake for 12-15 mins, until firm and golden. Let cool in pan for 5 mins.
Place a sheet of parchment paper over a damp tea towel. Sift a thick layer of powdered sugar over top. Turn cake out onto parchment paper and trim edges. Roll up loosely and let cool.
Meanwhile, for the filling, bring apricots, sugar and 8 tbsp water to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 mins. Remove from heat and let cool.
Gently unroll cake. Using a palette knife, spread apricot mixture evenly over cake then roll up again. Place on a serving plate and dust with more powdered sugar, if desired.

title: apple, cranberry and pear juice
directions: Using an electric juicer, juice apples, pears and cranberries. Pour into 2 glasses to serve.

title: pork chops with caramelized apple and cream sauce
directions: For the sauce, melt the butter in a large frying pan. Add the apples and cook, stirring, for 5 mins until lightly browned. Add the sugar and cook for 4-5 mins over low heat until the apples caramelize. Stir in the sherry and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer for 2-3 mins until the liquid has almost evaporated. Stir in the cream and simmer for 1-2 more mins until slightly thickened. Stir in the pecans and sage leaves.
Meanwhile, brush a griddle pan with the oil and preheat over high heat. Cook the cutlets for 3-4 mins on each side, until cooked through. Serve with sauce, mashed potatoes, and salad.

title: chicken skewers with tomato salad
directions: In a shallow dish, combine 1 tbsp olive oil, lemon zest, lemon juice, coriander and garlic. Add chicken and season to taste. Cover and marinate for 10 mins.
Combine finely chopped onion and vinegar in a bowl. Set aside.
Preheat grill. Thread cubed onion onto 8 soaked bamboo skewers alternately with chicken. Cook skewers for 8-10 mins, turning, until cooked through.
Meanwhile, combine tomatoes, olives, onion mixture and parsley. Add remaining oil and season. Serve skewers with tomato salad and mayonnaise.

title: flourless chocolate roulade
directions: Preheat oven to 180°C/160°C fan/gas 4. Grease a 25 x 30cm Swiss roll tin; line base with baking paper.
Combine chocolate, half the coffee granules and 60ml hot water in a large heatproof bowl. Stir over large saucepan of simmering water until smooth; remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks and 110g caster sugar in small bowl with electric mixer until thick and creamy; fold egg mixture into warm chocolate mixture.

Meanwhile, beat egg whites in small, clean bowl with electric mixer until soft peaks form; fold egg whites, in 2 batches, into chocolate mixture. Spread into prepared tin; bake for 10 mins, or until a skewer comes out clean.

Place a piece of baking paper cut a little larger than the Swiss roll tin on work surface; sprinkle evenly with 1 tbsp caster sugar. Turn cake on to sugared paper, peel lining paper away; use serrated knife to cut away crisp edges from all sides. Cover cake with tea towel; cool.

Dissolve remaining coffee granules in 1 tsp hot water in small bowl. Add cream, liqueur and sifted icing sugar; beat with electric mixer until firm peaks form. Spread cake evenly with three-quarters of the cream mixture. Roll cake, from long side, by lifting paper and using it to guide the roll into shape.
Spoon remaining cream in dollops along top of roll. Decorate with coffee beans. Cover roll; refrigerate for 30 mins before serving.

title: fruity iced tea
directions: Put the teabags in a large heatproof jug with the honey and add 2 litres boiling water. Leave to infuse for 1 hour.
Cut the melon into small chunks, discarding the seeds and skin. Thread half the melon onto skewers with some of the raspberries and nectarines. Add the remaining fruit to the tea.
Add plenty of ice to the jug. Pour into glasses and serve with the fruit skewers.

title: fig tart with honey crumbles
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Mix 2 3/4 cups of the flour, sugar, salt, egg and 1 stick butter with the dough hook of a electric mixer until blended. Roll out the pastry on a floured surface into a 9 x 12 inch rectangle. Press into a greased 8 x 11 inch rectangular tart pan. Trim edges. Line the pastry with parchment paper and fill with dried beans. Bake the pastry for 10 mins. Remove the parchment paper and beans. Bake 5 mins longer.

Meanwhile, mix remaining 1 cup flour, 5 tbsp butter and honey until coarse crumbs form. Set aside. Mix the mascarpone, egg yolks, orange peel, liqueur and vanilla extract until smooth. Place the figs in the tart pan. Pour the mascarpone mixture over the top. Sprinkle with the crumble mixture.
Bake 30 mins longer. Cool tart in the pan on a wire rack. Sprinkle with the pine nuts.

title: zabaglione with fresh berries
directions: Combine orange zest, orange juice and powdered sugar. Add berries and toss to combine. Set aside to macerate.

Meanwhile, to make the zabaglione, whisk egg yolks and sugar over a double boiler until starting to thicken. Slowly whisk in marsala. Cook, whisking, for 10 mins, or until soft peaks form and mixture has tripled in size and is thick and glossy.
Distribute berries between serving glasses and cover with zabaglione.

title: sparkling blue new year's eve cocktail
directions: Rim each cocktail glass with lemon juice then sugar. Decorate with a cocktail cherry and a few mint leaves. Mix the rum and curacao with crushed ice and pour into cocktail glasses. Top with pineapple juice and champagne.

title: butternut squash with sage
directions: Heat oil in a large frying pan and fry whole sage leaves until crispy. Drain on paper towels. Add squash and chopped sage to pan and saute over medium heat for 5-10 mins, until soft. Serve garnished with fried sage leaves.

title: peach granola loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and line base and sides of an 8x4 inch loaf pan with parchment paper, leaving extra at the long sides. For the batter, sift flour into a large bowl and stir in oats and sugar. Whisk buttermilk, 1 tbsp water, egg, vanilla, oil and reserved peach juice in a large bowl then stir into flour mixture.

Roughly chop half the peaches. Add peaches and cranberries to batter then stir until just combined. Spoon into prepared pan, smooth the surface and arrange remaining peach slices on top. Bake for 45-50 mins or until a skewer inserted in center comes out clean. Place pan on a wire rack and brush warm loaf with fruit spread. Cool in pan for 10 mins then transfer to wire rack to cool completely.

title: beef, mushroom and guinness pot pies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F.
Line pie shells with parchment paper and fill with pie weights. Bake blind for 10 mins. Remove paper and weights and bake for another 5 mins. Let cool.

Meanwhile, heat 1 tbsp olive oil in a large saucepan over high heat. Toss beef in flour then saute for 3-4 mins, until browned. Set aside. Add remaining oil and saute mushrooms and onion for 3-4 mins, until onion is tender. Add tomato paste and garlic. Cook for 1 min. Return beef to pan along with Guinness, stock and bay leaf. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, for 1 hour, stirring occasionally, until beef is tender. Let cool and discard bay leaf.

Distribute filling between pie shells. Brush edges with egg. Drape puff pastry over top and trim edges. Press edges with a fork to seal then brush tops lightly with egg. Cut a small air vent in the center of each pie and bake for 20-25 mins, until puffed and golden brown.

title: chocolate mousse cake
directions: Line a 7 inch springform pan with the chocolate cake, flattening with your hands to fill.
Combine heavy cream and chocolate over low heat, stirring, for 3 mins, or until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth. Add liqueur. Chill for 1 hour.

Beat chocolate mousse for 1-2 mins, or until mixture is thick. Transfer to prepared pan, smooth surface and chill for 3 hours, or until set. Transfer to a serving platter and dust with cocoa powder. Top with berries and serve.

title: salmon patties
directions: Cook potatoes in a saucepan of boiling water for 15 mins, until tender. Drain and return to pan on low heat for 2 mins until dry. Remove potatoes from heat and mash lightly. Add butter and hot milk, beating until smooth. Set aside to cool completely.
Flake salmon into a bowl. Add potato and Parmesan. Season, mix well and shape into eight patties. Place on a tray and chill for 1 hour.
Dust patties with flour. Brush with egg and coat with breadcrumbs. Heat oil in a skillet on medium. Cook patties for 3-5 mins each side until golden. Serve with salad and lemon wedges.

title: crab and pea spaghetti
directions: Cook the pasta in a saucepan of boiling, salted water according to package directions. Drain, then return to the pan. Pour boiling water over the peas. Let stand for 5 mins. Drain. Using back of a fork, crush the peas. Add the peas to the pasta.
Meanwhile, heat the oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Add the garlic and cook, stirring, for 30 seconds or until fragrant. Stir in 1 tbsp of the lemon peel.
Add the garlic mixture, lemon juice, crabmeat and parsley to the pasta and toss to combine. Serve topped with the remaining lemon peel and Parmesan cheese.

title: baked cannelloni
directions: Cook cannelloni in boiling, salted water until al dente. Drain then rinse under cold water. Drain again and set aside.
Preheat oven to 400°F. Grease a 12x8 inch baking dish. Combine tomato puree and stock. Pour 1/2 into prepared dish. Set aside.

Combine ground beef, ricotta, 1/2 of the Parmesan, olive oil and parsley. Season. Stuff cannelloni with ground beef mixture. Arrange in a single layer in prepared dish. Pour remaining tomato mixture over top. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan and bake for 30 mins. Sprinkle oregano leaves over top and cook for another 10 mins, until bubbling and golden. Serve hot.

title: tomato & olive chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Push half the thyme into the chicken cavity. Season the outside of the chicken. Place in a large baking dish.

Heat 2 tbsp of the reserved sun-dried tomato oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Add the shallots and garlic; saute for 3 mins. Remove from the heat. Stir in the tomato puree, wine, tomatoes, sun-dried tomatoes and paste, olives, pine nuts and remaining thyme. Season with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Pour over the chicken. Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour 10 mins. Remove foil. Bake for a further 20 mins, basting with the juices, until chicken is cooked through.

title: eggplant and almond chicken
directions: Heat 2 tbsp of the oil in large skillet on high heat. Saute eggplant, onion and garlic 4-5 mins, until golden.
Stir in tomato paste and spices and cook 1-2 mins, until fragrant.
Add tomatoes and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium. Simmer 5-10 mins, stirring occasionally, until sauce thickens. Season to taste.
Meanwhile, heat remaining 1 tbsp oil in a large skillet on high heat. Cook chicken 5-6 mins each side until completely cooked through.
Serve chicken with sauce and sprinkle with almonds. Accompany with arugula salad.

title: cream of porcini soup
directions: Heat the butter in a saucepan, add the onions and saute for 4-5 mins. Pour in the wine and bring to a boil. Add the porcini and soaking liquid to the pan. Bring to a boil. Add the cornstarch slurry and heavy cream to the pan. Simmer, stirring, until the sauce thickens. Season. Blend the soup until smooth using an immersion blender. Divide between 4 bowls and sprinkle with chives and Parmesan cheese.

title: caramelized pears with sugared tortillas
directions: In a large nonstick frying pan, melt butter over medium-high heat, until foamy. Add pears and cook, turning occasionally, for 4-5 mins, until tender. Add 1/3 cup water and 1/4 cup sugar. Cook, turning occasionally, for 7-8 mins, until caramelized and golden brown. Remove from heat and set aside.
Meanwhile, brush tortilla wedges with oil then coat in remaining sugar. Heat a medium nonstick frying pan over high heat. Cook tortillas for 1-2 mins per side, until golden brown.

Place 1 tortilla wedge on each serving plate. Top with a little caramelized pear and syrup then a dollop of whipped cream. Top with remaining tortilla wedges, pears and syrup, reserving a little syrup. Top with more whipped cream and drizzle with reserved syrup. Serve immediately.

title: veal stroganoff pies with carrot salad
directions: Toss veal in flour, shaking off excess. Heat 1 tbsp oil in a large saucepan over high heat. Cook veal, in batches, until browned. Remove from pan.
Add remaining oil to pan and reduce heat to medium. Cook shallots and mushrooms, stirring, until softened. Return veal to pan along with paprika. Cook, stirring, for 1 min, or until fragrant.

Add brandy then bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 min, or until reduced by 1/2. Add tomato paste and stock. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours, or until veal is tender. Stir in creme fraiche and season to taste. Let cool.
Preheat oven to 425°F. Oil 4 (4 1/2 inch) tart pans. Cut 4 (5 inch) circles from puff pastry. Cut 4 (5 1/2 inch) discs from pie dough and use to line base and sides of pan. Trim edges.

Divide veal mixture between pie shells. Brush edges with egg then top with puff pastry rounds. Press edges to seal and brush tops lightly with egg. Make 2 (1 inch) slits in the top of each lid. Place pies on a baking tray. Bake for 30 mins, or until browned. Let cool slightly before serving.
Meanwhile, place baby carrots on a baking tray. Sprinkle with butter and season. Bake for 25 mins, alongside pies.

Boil, steam or microwave larger carrots and green beans, separately, until tender. Drain. Combine carrots, green beans, baby carrots and any roasting juices. Season to taste. Serve pies with carrot mixture.

title: tomato, shrimp and pesto turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Grease and line 2 baking trays with parchment paper.

Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Cook onion and garlic for 5 mins, or until onion is soft. Add tomatoes and tomato paste. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 mins, or until sauce is thickened. Add fish and shrimp. Cook for 5 mins, or until fish is almost cooked through. Remove from heat and stir in spinach and pesto. Let cool for 10 mins.

Place puff pastry on prepared trays. Distribute seafood mixture between puff pastry, leaving a 3/4 inch border. Fold dough over to enclose filling and press edges with a fork to seal. Brush with egg and bake for 20 mins, or until golden brown.
Serve immediately with arugula.

title: fish, dill and arugula stew
directions: Mix the fish and lemon juice together and season. Set aside. Heat the oil in a pan, add the onion and saute for 3-4 mins, stirring. Mix in the fish and cook for 4-5 mins. Add the carrot, leek and pickles to the pan and stir to combine. Season. Add the stock and cream and bring to a boil. Simmer for 8-10 mins over low heat, stirring occasionally. Mix the cornstarch slurry into the sauce and simmer for 1-2 mins. Mix in the arugula and dill.
To serve, cook the rice according to the package instructions. Divide the fish stew and rice between 2 plates then serve.

title: individual gluten free egg, bacon and parmesan tarts
directions: To make the Parmesan tart dough, combine flour, cornstarch, cheese and butter in a food processor. Pulse until coarsely grated. Add enough ice water (around 2-3 tbsp) to make ingredients come together. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 30 mins.
Preheat oven to 425°F. Oil a 6-cup deep muffin pan.
Roll pastry out until 1/4 inch thick. Cut 6 (4 inch) rounds from pastry and use to line recesses. Prick bases with fork. Bake for 10 mins, or until golden brown. Let cool in pan.
Reduce oven to 400°F.
Heat oil in a small frying pan over medium heat. Cook bacon, onion and garlic, stirring, until bacon is soft. Distribute between tart shells.
Whisk eggs and cream together then stir in cheese and chives. Distribute between tart shells and bake for 25 mins, or until set.

title: shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F.

Cream butter until it resembles whipped cream. Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add flour and mix until very smooth. Shape into two 9 1/2 inch discs. Transfer to baking trays. Stretch dough out until very smooth. Level surface with a rolling pin. Crimp edges.

Score a circle in the center of dough with 2 3/4 inch cookie cutter then score into 12 wedges, from circle to outer edges. Prick with a fork and dust lightly with sugar. Bake for 40 mins, until very light brown and crisp. Let cool completely on trays. Break into wedges to serve.

title: chicken, artichoke and lemon skewers
directions: Combine lemon zest, lemon juice, olive oil and garlic. Thread chicken, artichokes and lemon wedges onto skewers then coat in marinade.
Lightly coat a grill pan with oil and place over medium heat. Cook skewers for 10 mins, turning regularly, until browned and chicken is cooked through.
Serve skewers with mixed greens.

title: chocolate brownie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease a deep 8 inch square cake pan and line base and sides with baking paper, extending paper 2 inches over sides.

Combine butter and semisweet chocolate in a medium saucepan. Stir over low heat until smooth. Let cool for 10 mins then stir in sugar and eggs. Fold in flour, white chocolate and milk chocolate. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 35 mins. Let cool in pan.

title: white bean dip
directions: Heat the oil in a medium skillet on medium heat. Cook the leek, stirring, for about 10 mins or until leek softens. Cool.
Blend or process the leek, beans, cream, lemon peel and juice until smooth. Stir in the parsley.

title: piri piri shrimp
directions: In a food processor, combine oil, herbs, zest, juice, chilies, garlic, and ginger. Process to a smooth paste. Season to taste.
In a medium bowl, combine 1/4 of the paste with shrimp. Place the remaining paste in a serving bowl. Marinate shrimp for at least 30 minutes.
Thread 3-4 prawns onto 2 skewers (through head and tail), so you can use skewers as handles to turn shrimp.

Heat an oiled outdoor grill or indoor grill pan to medium. Cook shrimp 2-3 minutes each side, until just cooked through. Serve scattered with more cilantro. Accompany with remaining sauce and lemon wedges.

title: autumn frittata skillet
directions: Preheat broiler to high.
In a large ovenproof skillet, heat butter and oil on high. Cook potatoes and pumpkin in 3 batches, 2-3 minutes each side, until golden and tender. Remove skillet from heat.
Arrange a layer of potatoes and pumpkin in skillet. Top with pancetta and half onion and herbs, then with remaining potatoes and pumpkin.
In a bowl, lightly beat eggs and water together. Season. Pour into skillet, shaking gently to distribute evenly.
Cook on medium, 4-5 minutes, until egg begins to set around edges. Transfer to broiler. Cook 4-5 minutes, until set in center. Sprinkle with remaining onions and herbs.

title: roast moroccan chicken
directions: Preheat broiler. Line a baking tray with parchment paper.
Cover chicken wings and ends of drumsticks with foil to prevent burning. Brush chicken with marinade and arrange on tray. Broil for 6-8 mins. Discard foil.
Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, prepare couscous according to package instructions. Add arugula and tomato.
Distribute couscous between serving plates. Arrange chicken on top and sprinkle with pistachios. Serve with lemon wedges.

title: southern slammer
directions: Spread the brown sugar on a saucer. Cut a slice from 1 lime and rub around the rim of each of eight cocktail glasses. Dip the rims into the sugar, then clean off any excess using the lime slice. Using a vegetable peeler, peel a length of zest that stretches two-thirds of the way around the lime. Thinly slice the lime and lime zest using a sharp knife to create a garnish.

Squeeze the juice from the remaining lime into a cocktail shaker. Add the Southern Comfort, grenadine and ice cubes and stir for 20-30 seconds until the mixture is extremely cold. Strain into the cocktail glasses and top each with a little champagne. Garnish with the prepared lime slices and zest and serve.

title: oysters with wasabi mayonnaise
directions: In a bowl, combine mayonnaise, lime zest, lime juice and wasabi paste.
Arrange oysters on a serving platter. Top with wasabi mayonnaise and julienned nori.

title: frozen strawberry margarita
directions: Combine liquor, lime juice and frozen strawberries in a blender with 6 ice cubes. Blend on high speed until smooth. Pour into a salt-rimmed 5 oz margarita glass. Decorate with a strawberry wedge.

title: linguine with basil and cherry tomatoes
directions: Cook the pasta according to package instructions.
Meanwhile, place oil and garlic in frying pan and heat slowly. Add tomatoes and basil and cook for 3 mins.
Drain pasta and add to frying pan. Toss well to combine. Sprinkle with Parmesan (if using) and season to taste.

title: apricot cheesecake
directions: Knead the flour, butter, almonds, powdered sugar, 2 tbsp water and a pinch of salt with the dough hook of a mixer, then with your hands, to a smooth dough. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for 2 hours.

Preheat the oven to 325°F. On a floured work surface, roll out the dough to an 11 inch diameter circle. Use it to line a 10 inch springform pan and press around the edges. Cut out a 10 inch diameter circle of parchment paper and lay over the pastry. Fill with baking beans and blind bake for 10-12 mins, until browned.

Meanwhile, beat the egg yolks, Marscapone, sour cream, custard powder and sugar with the whisk of a mixer. In a separate bowl, beat the egg whites until forming stiff peaks. Fold in batches into the egg yolk mixture.

Remove the shell from the oven and remove the beans and paper. Arrange the apricot wedges all over the base. Spoon over the egg mixture and smooth out. Bake at the same temperature for 30 mins. Allow to cool.
In a saucepan, heat the jam until smooth. Allow to cool for 5 mins, then drizzle over the cheesecake. Sprinkle over the pistachios and serve.

title: chocolate cherry french toast
directions: Place cherries, granulated sugar and lemon juice in a medium saucepan on medium heat. Cook and stir until sugar dissolves. Bring to a simmer; simmer for 10 mins or until cherries are just soft. Remove from heat. Cool.
Spread 6 bread slices with chocolate hazelnut spread; top with remaining bread slices. Whisk eggs and cream in a large bowl.

Heat half the butter in a large skillet on medium-low heat. Dip 3 of the sandwiches into egg mixture; turn to coat evenly. Cook for 10 mins, turning once, or until golden and cooked. Transfer to serving plates. Cut in half. Repeat with remaining butter, sandwiches and egg mixture. Serve warm French toast with cherry syrup, dusted with powdered sugar.

title: mixed berry and chicken salad
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet on high heat. Cook chicken for 4-5 mins, each side, until browned and cooked through. Cool and slice thinly.
Toss chicken with remaining ingredients, except almonds, in a large bowl.
For the dressing, place all ingredients in a food processor or blender. Process until smooth. Season to taste. Drizzle dressing over salad just before serving. Sprinkle with almonds.

title: warm chicken and lentil salad
directions: Cook the lentils for about 20 mins in a medium saucepan of boiling water; drain.

Meanwhile, combine the chicken, lemon peel, garlic and half the oregano in a small bowl. Lightly spray a heated large skillet with no stick cooking spray. Cook the chicken, stirring, until cooked through. Remove the chicken from the pan; keep warm.
Spray pan with cooking spray. Cook the vegetables and mushrooms, stirring, until softened.
Combine the lentils, chicken, vegetable mixture and spinach with remaining oregano and lemon juice in a large bowl.

title: za'atar crusted chicken
directions: In a small bowl, whisk oil, spice mix, lemon and seasoning together.
Place chicken pieces in a large zip-top bag and pour marinade over, tossing to coat well. Seal bag and marinate for 1 hour or overnight.
Preheat the oven to 400°F. Remove chicken from marinade. Transfer to a rack in a baking dish. Sprinkle with salt. Pour a little water into dish to cover base.
Bake chicken for 40-45 mins, until chicken is golden and cooked through. Serve with lemon wedges and salad.

title: crisp roasted potatoes
