directions: Preheat the oven to 425°F. Lightly oil a baking tray.
Boil, steam or microwave the potatoes for 5 mins then drain. Pat dry with paper towels and leave to cool for 10 mins.

Gently rake the rounded sides of the potatoes with the tines of a fork and place the potatoes in a single layer, cut-side down, on the baking tray. Brush with oil, season, then roast, uncovered, in the oven for about 50 mins or until the potatoes are browned and crisp. Serve hot

title: rainbow cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl with an electric mixer, until light and creamy. Add condensed milk; beat until well blended.
Sift flour and cocoa powder over mixture; stir until well combined.
Divide dough into 2 portions. Roll each portion in parchment paper to form an 11 inch log. Refrigerate for 30 mins.
Preheat the oven to 350°F. Line baking pans with parchment paper.
Cut each log into 1/3 inch thick slices. Place 2 inches apart on prepared pans. Press chocolate chips onto each cookie.
Bake for 10-12 mins or until lightly golden. Cool on pans for 2 mins. Remove from pans; cool completely on wire racks.

title: lamb meatloaf with baked eggs and middle eastern spice
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Lightly grease an 8x4 inch loaf pan.
In a large bowl, combine lamb, herbs, breadcrumbs, onion, beaten egg, chile and 2 tsp za'atar, and remaining spices. Season to taste; mix well.
Press mixture into pan. Make two indentations in top of mixture. Crack whole eggs and gently pour an egg into each hole. Sprinkle 2 tbsp za'atar around eggs.
Cover loosely with foil. Bake 45 minutes. Uncover; bake a further 5-10 minutes, until cooked through and egg is set. Let cool 10 minutes before slicing.
Serve meatloaf accompanied by tabouli, flatbread, and yogurt.

title: vegetable tarts with tomato sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Oil 2-3 baking trays.

Combine tomatoes, sugar, 3 tbsp oil and 1 tbsp vinegar in a large bowl. Arrange tomatoes, skin-side down, on a baking tray and roast for 1 hour 40 mins. Remove from oven and return to same bowl. Crush with a potato masher and cover to keep warm.

Place peppers, skin-side up, on a baking tray. Roast for 40 mins, or until softened. Transfer to a plastic bag and close tightly. Let cool then peel skin and discard membrane and seeds. Slice flesh thinly.

Meanwhile, melt butter in a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Cook zucchini, stirring, for 5 mins, or until softened. Transfer to a small bowl and cover to keep warm. Add mushrooms and garlic to pan. Cook, stirring, for 5 mins, or until mushrooms soften. Add port and cook, stirring, until liquid evaporates.

Cut 2 puff pastry sheets into 4 (6 inch) squares. Cut remaining sheet into 4 (4 inch) squares. Place small squares on a baking tray. Distribute mushroom mixture, zucchini and peppers between centers, leaving a 3/4 inch border. Whisk together egg yolk and milk. Brush edges with egg wash and top with large squares, pressing edges together to seal.
Using a sharp knife, cut around tarts, leaving a 1/4 inch border. Score the pastry with a swirl design, starting from the center. Brush with egg wash and bake for 25 mins.
Meanwhile, toss spinach with remaining oil and vinegar in a small bowl.
Serve tarts with tomato sauce and spinach salad.

title: beef and leek lasagna
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Grease a 10 x 7 inch baking dish. Heat the oil in a saucepan and fry the ground beef over high heat until crumbly. Add the tomato puree, onion, garlic, carrot and oregano and fry for 1 min. Season with salt, black pepper and a pinch of sugar. Add the chopped tomatoes and 1/2 cup stock, bring to a boil and simmer over low heat for 10 mins.

To make the bechamel sauce, melt the butter in a separate saucepan. Stir in the flour and saute for 2 mins. Gradually stir in the milk and the rest of the stock. Bring to a low boil, stirring constantly, and simmer for 8 mins. Season with salt, black pepper and nutmeg.

Blanch the leeks in boiling salted water for 2 mins. Drain and refresh with cold water. Spread 1/4 of the bechamel sauce in the baking dish, then add 3 sheets lasagna, half the leeks and half the ground beef. Repeat, then top with the remaining noodles and sauce. Sprinkle with the cheese, then bake for 40-45 mins, until golden and bubbling. Garnish with fresh oregano.

title: chilled mint zucchini soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat 1 tbsp oil. Cook onion over medium heat for 5 mins, until soft. Add garlic. Cook for 1 min. Add zucchini, cover and cook over low heat for 10 mins, until zucchini has softened. Add 5 cups water and mint. Season. Bring to a boil then cover, reduce heat to low and simmer for 20 mins. Let cool for 5 mins then puree until smooth. Chill for at least 4 hours, or overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°F. Toss bread with remaining oil and lemon zest. Place on a baking tray and bake for 15 mins, until crisp and golden.
Serve chilled soup with croutons and extra mint.

title: meatball sub
directions: Preheat broiler. Combine ground meat, 3 cloves garlic, breadcrumbs, Parmesan, Worcestershire and egg. Using damp hands, shape mixture into 24 meatballs. Heat 1/2 tbsp oil in a frying pan over medium heat, cook meatballs, in batches, for 3 mins, or until browned. Set aside.

Reduce heat, add remaining oil and cook remaining garlic, stirring, for 30 seconds, or until fragrant. Add tomato puree and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 5 mins, or until sauce thickens slightly. Return meatballs to pan and coat in sauce. Cover and simmer for 5 mins, or until meatballs are cooked.

Using a serrated knife, cut a 1/3 inch slice horizontally off top of bread. Place both pieces of bread, cut-side up, on a large baking tray. Top bread base with spinach then meatball mixture. Sprinkle with cheese then broil for 2 mins, or until golden. Transfer to a chopping board. Add top piece of bread and sandwich together. Cut into 4 equal pieces. Serve with mixed greens.

title: garlic and herb mushrooms
directions: Melt 3 tbsp of the butter in a large heavy-bottomed skillet on high heat. Add mushrooms and garlic; cook, stirring, for 5-6 mins until the mushrooms are soft and golden. Remove from heat. Add 3 tbsp of the parsley and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper.
Mix 2 tbsp butter with remaining 1 tbsp parsley and place on top of the hot mushrooms just before serving.

title: crostini two ways
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Toast crostini in oven for 8-10 mins. Let cool. For the balsamic reduction, bring vinegar and sugar to a boil, stirring. Reduce heat and simmer for 5 mins, until slightly thickened. Let cool.
In a food processor, blend anchovies, capers, olives, garlic and 3 tbsp olive oil into a paste. Season. Set aside. Heat remaining oil in a pan and saute chorizo. Add thyme. Set aside.
Spread anchovy and olive tapenade over 1/2 of crostini. Top with chorizo and thyme. Arrange sliced Brie and figs on remaining crostini and drizzle with balsamic reduction. Serve immediately.

title: meatballs with tomato sauce and french fries
directions: Squeeze out the bread and place in a bowl along with the beef, tomato puree, egg and half the onions. Season with salt and black pepper and knead together. Form into 8 balls.

Heat 1 tbsp olive oil in a saucepan and saute the peppers and remaining onion for 5 mins. Remove half the mixture from the pan and set aside. Add the tomatoes and 3/4 cup water to the pan. Stir in the bouillon, cover and simmer for 10 mins.

Heat the vegetable oil in a saucepan or deep fryer to 300°F. Fry the french fries in batches for 3 mins each. Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels. Increase the temperature to 325°F and fry the potatoes again in batches for 5 mins each. Drain on paper towels, season with salt and keep warm.

Meanwhile, heat 2 tbsp olive oil in a skillet and saute the meatballs for 10 mins, turning. Transfer the peppers and tomato sauce to a blender and puree. Season with salt and black pepper and stir in the reserved onion and pepper mixture. Serve the meatballs and french fries with the sauce ladled over.

title: beef casserole with vegetables
directions: Cook the beef in a frying pan with no oil 5 mins. Add onion and cook 5 more mins. Add tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce and season. Bring to a boil then cover and simmer 20 mins.
Cook the carrots and potatoes in boiling salted water 10-15 mins until tender. Drain. Mash and season carrots. In a separate bowl, mash potatoes with the butter and milk and season.
Preheat oven to 400°F. Layer beef, carrot, spinach and potatoes in a deep ovenproof dish. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 25-30 mins until golden. Serve hot.

title: curried chutney pork
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet on high heat. Cook pork 3-4 mins, turning, to sear well. Stir in curry powder; cook 1 min, until fragrant.
Stir in cream and mango chutney. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium. Simmer 1-2 mins, stirring, until thickened.
Add broccolini; simmer 2-3 mins, until just tender. Serve with additional chutney and pappadums or naan bread.

title: raspberry galette
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°C. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Place pie crust on pan.

Mix raspberries, granulated sugar, flour, hazelnuts and vanilla in a medium bowl. Spoon raspberry mixture into center of crust, leaving a 2 inch border. Fold edge of crust up over filling, pleating the crust as needed. Brush pie crust with egg, then sprinkle raspberry mixture with demerara sugar.
Bake for 25 minutes or until golden. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: chicken on warm lentil salad
directions: Heat half the oil in a frying pan over high heat and cook the chicken, turning, until browned on both sides and cooked through. Cover to keep warm.
Heat the rest of the oil in a medium saucepan and stir in the onion, bacon and garlic over medium heat until the bacon is browned and the onion is soft.

Add the wine and cook until the wine is almost evaporated. Add the stock and lentils and cook until the lentils are hot and the stock is reduced by half. Remove from heat, then add the tomatoes and parsley, stirring gently to combine.
Serve the chicken over the warm lentil salad.

title: chicken campagnola
directions: Preheat broiler.

Heat oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Add capers and garlic and cook for 1 min. Add chicken and cook for 2-3 mins per side, until golden brown. Add lemon juice and simmer for 30 seconds. Top each piece of chicken with tomatoes and mozzarella.
Transfer to oven and broil for 1 min, until cheese bubbles and melts. Serve with baby spinach and basil.

title: bircher muesli
directions: Combine oats, grated apple, apple juice, milk and 1/2 cup yogurt. Cover with plastic wrap and chill overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°F. Spread nuts over a baking tray and bake for 4-5 mins, until lightly toasted. Let cool then roughly chop.
Distribute muesli between serving bowls. Top with berries, toasted nuts and remaining yogurt. Serve.

title: lamb bourguignon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Coat lamb in flour, shaking off excess. Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over high heat. Working in batches, sear lamb. Remove from pan.

Reduce heat to medium and add butter. Cook shallots, bacon, mushrooms and garlic, stirring, until lightly browned. Return lamb to pan along with remaining ingredients and 1 cup water. Bring to a boil then cover and transfer to oven to braise for 1 hour 30 mins. Uncover and cook for another 30 mins, or until lamb is tender and sauce has thickened slightly.

title: hazelnut ice cream
directions: In a food processor, combine nuts, milk, sugar and liqueur. Process until smooth. Strain, pressing out oils and liquid with the back of a metal spoon.
Whip heavy cream and chocolate hazelnut spread to soft peaks. Fold through hazelnut mixture, until well combined.
Transfer to a large container, smooth surface and cover with plastic wrap. Freeze for 4 hours, or until firm. Serve sprinkled with reserved chopped nuts, if desired.

title: mango baked alaska
directions: Combine ice cream and puree in a large bowl and stir until combined. Return to ice cream container and freeze overnight.
Scoop 8 balls of ice cream and place on a frozen tray. Freeze for 2 hours, until firm.
Using a 2 1/2 inch round cutter, cut cake into 8 rounds. Arrange on a large baking tray. Drizzle with orange juice and Cointreau then top with mango slices and ice cream balls. Freeze.
Preheat oven to 425°F.
To make the meringue, in a stand mixer, whip egg whites to soft peaks. Gradually add sugar, beating well between additions, until dissolved.
Working quickly, spread meringue over ice cream rounds. Bake for 1-2 mins, until meringue is browned lightly. Serve immediately.

title: breaded chicken with corn salad
directions: Line a baking tray with parchment paper. Whisk egg whites and milk in a shallow bowl. Place flour and crumbs on separate plates. Dust chicken with flour, shaking off excess. Dip in egg whites then in crumbs to coat evenly. Place on prepared tray, cover with plastic wrap and chill for 15 mins.
Preheat oven to 375°F. Spray chicken all over with oil. Bake for 40 mins, or until golden and cooked through.

Meanwhile, preheat grill. Lightly coat corn with oil. Grill for 8-10 mins, or until browned and tender. Transfer to a chopping board. Let cool slightly then cut into rounds. Transfer to a large bowl. Add tomatoes, radishes, onion and parsley. Whisk together lemon juice, mustard and garlic then drizzle over salad and toss to combine.
Spoon salad onto serving plates and top with chicken. Serve immediately.

title: baby arugula quiche
directions: For the pastry, process the flour and butter until crumbly. Add the egg yolk and 2 tbsp ice-cold water and pulse until the ingredients come together. Knead the pastry on a floured surface until smooth. Cover and refrigerate for 20 mins.

Grease an 8-inch round tart pan with removable bottom. Roll the pastry on a floured surface until large enough to line prepared pan. Press the pastry into bottom and side of the pan; trim edges. Refrigerate for 20 mins.

Preheat the oven to 400°F. Place the tart pan on a baking pan. Line pastry with parchment paper and fill with baking beans. Bake for 12 mins; remove paper and beans. Bake for 8 mins or until the pastry is browned; cool. Reduce the oven to 325°F.
Sprinkle the arugula in the crust. Whisk the eggs, egg yolk and cream in a medium bowl. Pour the mixture over the arugula.
Bake for about 40 mins or until set. Cool.

title: salsa verde
directions: In a food processor, process all ingredients until well combined. Season to taste.

title: salmon and summer vegetables with chermoula
directions: For the chermoula, blend or process herbs, garlic, red pepper flakes and ground spices until combined. Add lemon juice and 1 tbsp of the oil; process until smooth. Transfer to a medium bowl; stir in yogurt. Season to taste.
Mix the onions, zucchini, asparagus and 1 tbsp of the oil in a large bowl. Heat a grill pan on high heat. Cook vegetables until charred and tender. Transfer to a plate and cover to keep warm.
Rub salmon with remaining 1 tbsp oil; season. Cook, skin-side down, in grill pan until skin is crispy. Turn and cook until just cooked through.
Serve salmon with chermoula and vegetables.

title: almond fingers (thaktila)
directions: Sift the flour into a large bowl. Stir in the olive oil, 1 cup water and egg yolks. Knead the dough on a floured work surface until smooth. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 30 mins.

Meanwhile, for the honey syrup, stir all ingredients and 2 cups water in a medium saucepan on medium heat until the sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to low; simmer, uncovered, without stirring, for about 15 mins or until the syrup is thick.
Combine the almonds, cinnamon and sugar in a medium bowl.

Divide the dough in half. Roll as thinly as possible. Cut into 4-inch squares. Place 2 tsp of the nut mixture along the center of each square. Brush the edges with a little egg white and roll into a cigar shape. Use a fork to press the ends to seal. Repeat with the remaining dough and nut mixture.

Place the vegetable oil in a large saucepan or wok on medium heat. Heat to 350°F (or until a cube of bread turns golden in 10 seconds). Deep-fry the pastries, 3 or 4 at a time, turning frequently, until lightly browned. Drain briefly on paper towels then submerge in the warm honey syrup. Drain on wire rack over a tray to catch the drips. Serve warm or cooled.

title: asian fish cabbage rolls
directions: Place fish fillets into a shallow dish. Pour lemon juice over fish and season to taste. Let stand for 5 mins.
Wash cabbage leaves and place on a large microwave-safe plate. Cover cabbage leaves with paper towels and microwave on high for 4 mins. Drain and allow to cool slightly.

For each cabbage rolls, place a cabbage leaf flat on a work surface. Top with a piece of fish, trimming to fit. Roll up from stalk end and fold sides in to form a neat parcel. Place seam-side down in shallow microwave-safe dish. Microwave, covered, on medium for 8-10 mins. Set aside.

Mix teriyaki sauce, soy sauce, mirin, sesame oil, onions, ginger and chili pepper in a medium microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on high for 1 min. Drain cabbage rolls and cut in half. Serve drizzled with sauce.

title: candied orange slices
directions: Bring a very large saucepan of salted water to a boil and add whole oranges. Return to a boil. Drain and rinse under cold water. Repeat twice more. Cut into 1/4 inch-thick slices and remove seeds.

Combine sugar and 10 cups water in same pan. Stir on low heat until sugar has dissolved; do not boil. Add orange slices; simmer for 2 hours, or until soft and very shiny. Stir in liqueur. Gently spoon slices into hot sterilized jars and seal while hot.

title: baked beans, bacon, tomato and chives
directions: Preheat broiler.
Heat beans in a small saucepan.
Meanwhile, cook bacon in a small frying pan over medium-high heat, turning, until crisp. Drain on paper towels.
Top toast with beans, bacon and tomatoes. Broil for about 2 mins, or until hot. Sprinkle with chives and serve.

title: turkish delight bars
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease and line a 12 x 8-inch baking pan with parchment paper, extending paper above long sides for handles.

Beat butter, sugar and vanilla in large bowl with electric mixer until combined. Stir in sifted flours. Press mixture evenly into bottom of prepared pan. Use a fork to rough the surface. Bake for 20 mins. Cool.
For the topping, sprinkle gelatin over 2 tbsp water in small heatproof bowl. Stand bowl in small saucepan of simmering water; stir until gelatin dissolves.

Stir 1/4 cup water and sugar in medium saucepan on low heat, without boiling, until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil. Boil, uncovered, without stirring, until temperature reaches 241°F on a candy thermometer. Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, for 5 mins, without stirring, adjusting heat to maintain temperature at 241°F. Remove from heat.

Mix cornstarch with 1 tbsp water, gelatin mixture, rosewater and a few drops of food color until smooth; stir into sugar syrup. Return to heat; simmer, stirring, for 3 mins or until mixture is opaque. Strain mixture over layer in pan, skimming surface as needed. Let stand for 3 hours or overnight at room temperature. Serve dusted with sifted powdered sugar.

title: croque monsieur baguette
directions: Using a serrated knife, cut baguette crossways into 24 slices.

Brush one side of each slice with butter; turn slices buttered-side down. Spread tops of all slices with mustard; sandwich pancetta and cheese between slices, keeping the buttered side on the outside.
Preheat a large sandwich press. Toast sandwiches for 5 mins or until golden and cheese is melted. Top with a cornichon, secure with a toothpick. Place on a platter to serve.

title: potatoes with mushroom ragout
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Prick potatoes with a fork, place on a baking sheet and sprinkle with sea salt. Bake for 60-75 mins, until soft when squeezed.

Meanwhile, heat oil in a frying pan and saute onion for 8 minutes, until browned. Add wine, chopped tomatoes, tomato puree and mushrooms and season to taste. Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Uncover and simmer for 5 minutes. Add chopped parsley.
Cut potatoes and top with mushroom mixture. Serve with sour cream, garnished with parsley and black pepper.

title: pepper pork medallions with cabbage
directions: Season the pork medallions with plenty of freshly ground black pepper then sprinkle with chili flakes. Heat the vegetable oil in a large heavy-based frying pan and fry the medallions over a medium high heat for 6-8 mins until browned and just cooked through, turning occasionally.

Meanwhile to make the salad, toss together the chopped cabbage and apples slices. Whisk together the mayonnaise, yogurt, apple juice, vinegar and parsley and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper. Pour most of the dressing over the salad and toss gently to coat.
Serve the pork medallions with the salad, sprinkled with the salad cress and with the rest of the salad dressing in a small bowl.

title: eggplant chutney
directions: Place eggplant in a colander. Sprinkle with salt and let stand for 30 mins. Rinse with cold water then pat dry with paper towels.

Combine eggplant, onion, tomatoes, pepper, garlic, vinegar and spices in a large saucepan. Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 45 mins, or until vegetables are pulpy. Stir in sugar and cook, stirring, over low heat, until sugar has dissolved.

title: veal with creamy thyme sauce
directions: Heated a large oiled frying pan over medium-high heat. Working in batches, cook veal steaks until browned on both sides. Cover to keep warm.
Add cream, mustard and thyme to pan and bring to a boil, stirring. Simmer, uncovered, for about 5 mins, or until sauce thickens slightly. Top veal with sauce to serve.

title: insalata caprese
directions: For the salsa verde: puree the herbs, garlic, lemon juice and oil in food processor into a smooth sauce. Season to taste.
Mix the onion, tomatoes, cherry tomatoes and mozzarella, drizzle with salsa verde. Serve garnished with mint and basil.

title: french onion and asparagus muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease a muffin pan.
Sift flour into a large bowl. Stir in onion soup mix. In a small bowl, whisk cream cheese with eggs. Mix in milk and melted butter. Add to flour, stirring until just combined.
Fold in asparagus. Spoon mixture evenly into muffin pan until two-thirds full. Bake muffins for 20-25 mins, until golden. Cool in pan for 5 mins before transferring to a wire rack.

title: tropical cherry-coconut cocktail
directions: Spread the coconut in a circle on a saucer. Rub the lemon around the rim of a cocktail glass to moisten, then dip the rim in the coconut. Place the cream, liqueur, cherry juice, cream of coconut and crushed ice in a blender and blend until smooth. Pour into the prepared glass, garnish with a cherry and serve.

title: amaretti peaches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Arrange peaches, cut-side up, in an oven safe dish. Combine cookie crumbs, ground almonds and cocoa in a bowl. Spoon liberally into each peach cavity.
Drizzle marsala over peaches and dot with butter. Bake for 10-15 minutes, until hot and bubbly. Serve peaches warm with mascarpone.

title: carrot cakes with date cream cheese frosting
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Generously grease a 6-cup Texas muffin pan.
Place raisins in a small heatproof bowl. Add 1/4 cup boiling water; let stand 10 mins.

Meanwhile, beat eggs, stevia, syrup, oil and vanilla extract in a large bowl with an electric mixer about 5 mins. Stir in carrot, raisins and soaking liquid, and pecans. Fold in sifted dry ingredients. Divide mixture evenly among muffin cups.
Bake for 35 mins or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan 5 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

Meanwhile, for the frosting, process dates and 2 tbsp boiling water until almost smooth, scraping down the side of the bowl. Add cream cheese and butter; process until frosting is light and fluffy, scraping down the side of the bowl. Spread frosting on cooled cakes.

title: sweet chili chicken and corn salad
directions: Place chicken in a glass dish. Whisk 2 tbsp oil, half the chili sauce and half the garlic in a bowl. Pour over chicken; turn to coat. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 30 mins to marinate.
Preheat grill to medium-high. Brush corn with 1 tbsp oil. Grill, turning several times, for 8-10 mins, until browned and tender. Transfer to a chopping board and cut into 1 inch-thick slices.

Remove chicken from marinade. Discard marinade. Grill chicken for 5 mins each side, or until browned and cooked through. Transfer to a plate. Cover with foil and let stand for 5 mins. Cut into thick slices.
Grill tomato halves, cut-side up, for 30 seconds, or until browned. Transfer to a plate. Grill lime halves, cut-side up, for 30 seconds, or until browned.

Whisk lime juice and remaining oil, sweet chilli sauce and garlic in a bowl. Stir in green onion and 1 tbsp water. Place lettuce, avocados, corn, chicken, tomato and limes on a platter. Drizzle with dressing and sprinkle with cilantro.

title: almond bars with apricot glaze
directions: Grease a microwave-safe 10 inch ring or bundt pan.
Cream butter and sugar for 3 mins, until light and fluffy. Add flour and stir until combined. Press firmly into prepared pan. Set aside.

For the filling, beat butter, sugar and orange zest until just combined. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Add ground almonds and stir until combined. Transfer to prepared pan then sprinkle sliced almonds over top. Microwave on MEDIUM for 5 mins.
Meanwhile, to make the apricot glaze, place jam in a small, microwave-safe bowl. Cover and microwave on HIGH for 1 min, until runny. Immediately brush over warm cake. Let cool in pan. Slice to serve.

title: classic fish and chips
directions: Heat oil in a large heavy-bottomed saucepan on medium heat (a cube of bread sizzles as soon as it is added). Cook chips in 2 batches, 4-5 mins each, until just tender but not browned. Drain on paper towels. Set aside 10 mins. Remove oil from heat.
For the batter, sift flour and cornstarch into a large bowl. Gradually whisk in beer and club soda to form a thin batter. Refrigerate 30 mins.
Reheat oil on high heat. Re-fry chips in batches, 4-5 mins, until crisp and golden brown. Drain on paper towels.

Reduce heat to medium. Dust fish in flour and dip into batter, wiping off excess. Gently lower into oil and cook in 2 batches, 3-4 mins each. Drain on paper towels. Serve fish and chips with lemon wedges and tartar sauce.

title: hawaii toast
directions: Heat oven to 425°F. Heat oil in a pan and brown the pork for about 2 mins on each side until cooked through. Season with salt and pepper then set aside.

For the apricot sauce, add the carrots to the pan and saute for 3 mins. Stir in the apricots and almonds and saute 3 more mins. Season with salt and pepper, stir in the jam to heat through, then remove from the heat.

To assemble, place the bread slices on a lined baking sheet. Top with the pork and apricot sauce. Sprinkle with cheese and bake for about 10 mins until the cheese is golden. Serve with a sprinkling of chopped parsley.

title: orange and poppy seed syrup cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease a deep 8 inch cake pan and line base and sides with parchment paper.
Combine poppy seeds and milk in a small bowl. Let stand for 20 mins.

Beat butter, orange zest and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time. Stir in flour, ground almonds, orange juice and poppy seed mixture. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 1 hour, or until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cool in pan for 5 mins then transfer to a wire rack set over a rimmed baking tray.

Meanwhile, to make the orange syrup, stir sugar, orange juice and 1/3 cup water over low heat, without boiling, until sugar has dissolved. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer, without stirring, for 2 mins. Pour hot syrup over hot cake.

title: köttbullar (swedish meatballs)
directions: Cook the potatoes in boiling salted water for about 20 mins.

Meanwhile, mix together the ground beef, onion, egg, breadcrumbs and spices. Season. With slightly damp hands, shape the mixture into about 48 small meatballs. Heat the oil in a large skillet and sear the meatballs for about 5 mins, turning them as necessary. Remove from the pan and keep warm. Pour the stock and cream into the hot pan and bring to a boil. Mix the flour with a little water until it is smooth and stir into the sauce. Simmer over low heat for about 5 mins and season it to taste.
Drain the potatoes and sprinkle them with the parsley. Serve the meatballs and sauce with the potatoes on the side.

title: cherry tomato, basil and crème fraîche tart with buckwheat crust
directions: In a food processor, combine flour, olive oil and a pinch of salt. Pulse until mixture resembles breadcrumbs. Add egg and pulse until combined. Gradually add 5 tbsp cold water, 1 tbsp at a time, until dough starts to come together in a ball.
Turn dough out onto a floured work surface and knead until soft. Cover in plastic wrap and chill for 20 mins.
Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease an 8 inch tart pan.

Roll out dough into a large circle, about 1/4 inch thick, and use to line tart pan. Trim edges and prick all over with a fork. Bake for 10-15 mins, or until light golden brown. Remove from oven and let cool completely.
Spoon creme fraiche into tart shell and smooth out. Arrange tomatoes on top and sprinkle with torn basil. Season.

title: chili shrimp with rice noodles
directions: Combine shrimp, garlic, sambal, peanut oil and chopped cilantro in a medium bowl. Season.
Place noodles in a medium heatproof bowl and cover with boiling water. Let stand until tender then drain.
Meanwhile, heat sesame oil in a wok. Stir-fry shrimp mixture until just pink. Add onions, cabbage, fish sauce, oyster sauce, sugar and noodles. Stir-fry until cabbage wilts.
Serve stir-fry topped with chili and fresh cilantro leaves.

title: broiled portobello mushrooms
directions: Preheat broiler to medium. Lay mushrooms, stalk side up, on a foil-lined broiler pan.
Combine oil, garlic and chili in a small bowl. Drizzle evenly over mushrooms. Broil for 10-15 minutes, until tender and juicy. Serve sprinkled with parsley.

title: baked stuffed eggplant
directions: Scoop out the flesh from each of the eggplants, leaving a 1/4 inch margin of flesh intact. Dice the removed flesh and mix with lemon juice. Heat 2 tbsp oil in a saucepan, add the onions and garlic and saute for 2-3 mins. Add the diced eggplant to the pan and continue to saute for 2-3 mins, stirring. Add the rice and white wine and simmer for 1 min, then stir in the stock. Cover the pan and simmer for 18-20 mins.
Preheat the oven to 350°F. Heat 1 tbsp oil in a skillet, add the pork and pan fry for 4-5 mins, turning. Remove from heat once cooked through.
Thinly slice 2 tomatoes and set aside for garnish. Dice 5 tomatoes and stir into the rice just before it is ready. Simmer for 2-3 mins, then stir in the pork slices and 2 tbsp butter. Season.

Grease a baking dish with some butter then place the eggplant halves inside. Spoon in the rice mixture then place the sliced tomatoes on top. Sprinkle with parmesan then place in the oven for 50 mins-1 hour. Cover with foil after 30-40 mins cooking time. Sprinkle with parsley before serving.

title: meat, potato and cabbage pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Blanch the cabbage in boiling water for 1 minute. Drain thoroughly.

Mix together the meat, onion, egg and a little salt and pepper. Slice the potatoes as thinly as possible and scatter half in the base of a shallow ovenproof dish. Layer the cabbage and meat mixture on top and finish with a layer of potatoes. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour the stock on top and cover with foil. Bake for 30 minutes. Remove the foil and bake for an additional 40-50 minutes until the potatoes are tender and pale golden.

title: five-spice lamb and chili stir-fry with greens
directions: Combine lamb and five-spice in medium bowl.
Heat lightly oiled wok on high heat. Stir-fry lamb, in batches, until browned. Remove from wok.
Add garlic and onion to wok; stir-fry about 5 mins or until onion softens. Add 1/4 cup water, broccolini, peas and mushrooms; stir-fry until vegetables are tender.
Return lamb to wok with 2 tbsp water and sauces; stir-fry until heated through. Season to taste. Serve stir-fry sprinkled with chili pepper.

title: seared scallop, endive and roquefort salad
directions: Arrange endive, cheese and hazelnuts on serving plates.
For the vinaigrette, whisk all ingredients in a small bowl. Season to taste.

Melt butter in a medium skillet on medium heat, until foaming. Lightly season scallops and add to pan. Cook for 30 seconds to 1 min, turn, cook for 30 seconds. Remove from pan and arrange on salad. Drizzle with vinaigrette and sprinkle with parsley to serve.

title: kiwi jelly
directions: Gently pulse kiwi in a blender and set aside. In a medium saucepan, combine sugar and 1 cup water and stir on low heat, until sugar has dissolved. Increase heat to high and boil 2 mins. Add kiwi and lime juice. Cover and cool 5 mins. Sprinkle in gelatin and stir until dissolved. Strain mixture through a fine sieve. Pour into small glasses or serving bowls and chill 3 hours, until set. Top with small scoops of sorbet to serve.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F. Lightly oil 2 baking trays.

Heat vegetable oil in a small frying pan over medium heat. Sweat onion until softened. Transfer to a large bowl. Dip bread in a small bowl of cold water then remove immediately. Transfer to bowl with onions. Add remaining ingredients and mix until combined. Distribute between centers of puff pastry then roll up to enclose filling. Place, seam-side down, on prepared trays. Brush with egg wash and sprinkle with sesame seeds. Cut each roll into 8 pieces. Bake for about 15 mins, or until golden brown.

title: cheese and herb omelet
directions: Whisk eggs and herbs in a medium bowl until well combined. Season to taste.

Melt a little butter in an omelet pan. Pour in a quarter of egg mixture. It should start to set around the edge almost immediately. Using a spatula, pull the edge of the omelet away from the side of the pan, allowing uncooked mixture to run underneath and cook.
When egg mixture no longer runs freely, top with 1/4 each of the cheese, spinach leaves and tomatoes.
Fold omelet in half to cover filling; slide onto plate. Serve hot with toast and prosciutto. Repeat with remaining egg mixture and filling.

title: coconut fruit cakes with buttercream frosting
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Grease two 6-cup Texas muffin pans.

Beat the butter and sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixer until light and creamy. Beat in the eggs, one by one, until combined. Stir in the sifted flours and coconut milk until combined. Stir in the ginger, cherries and pineapple. Spoon into the prepared pans, smoothing the tops.
Bake for 35-40 mins or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pans 5 mins. Remove from pans; cool completely on wire rack.

Meanwhile, for the frosting, beat the butter in a medium bowl with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Beat in the powdered sugar and milk until pale and creamy. Spoon into a piping bag fitted with a 1/3 inch star tip.
Pipe the frosting onto the tops of the cooled cupcakes to cover. Sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: sweet potato and ricotta terrine with spicy tomato sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease and line an 8x4 inch loaf pan with parchment paper.
Toss sweet potato and oil in a baking pan. Season. Roast for 25-30 mins, shaking occasionally, until golden brown. Let cool.

Combine ricotta, egg yolks, green onions, thyme, lemon zest and lemon juice. Season. Add sweet potato and toss to combine. Whip egg whites to soft peaks then fold in. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 45-50 mins, until firm to the touch.

Meanwhile, to make the spicy tomato sauce, heat oil in a frying pan over medium heat. Saute onion and garlic for 1 min, until tender. Add tomatoes, sugar, mustard and garam masala. Reduce heat and simmer for 5 mins, until thick.
Serve terrine, sliced, with spicy tomato sauce, salad and crusty bread.

title: chocolate melting moments
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease 2 baking pans and line with parchment paper.
Beat butter and sifted powdered sugar in medium bowl with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Spoon mixture into piping bag fitted with 1/2-inch star tip. Pipe stars about 2 inches apart on prepared pans.
Bake about 10 mins. Cool in pan 2 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack. Sandwich cookies with chocolate hazelnut spread.

title: spiced lamb turkish pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F.

Heat oil in a frying pan over high heat. Cook onion and carrot for 4 mins. Add ground lamb and cook for 3 mins, until browned. Add garlic and spices. Cook for 2 mins, until ground lamb is almost cooked through. Season and remove from heat.
Arrange flatbread on a baking tray. Distribute lamb mixture between flatbreads and top with spinach and mozzarella. Bake for 15 mins, until flatbreads are crisp and cheese is bubbling and golden.
Serve with lemon wedges. Enjoy!

title: gluten-free cappuccino cakes
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Line a 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners. Sift the flour into a large bowl. Stir in the sugar. Make a well in the center.
Whisk the butter, eggs, milk and vanilla in medium bowl. Pour the egg mixture into the dry ingredients and mix until just combined. Spoon into the muffin cups.
Bake for 25-30 mins or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan 5 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

For the icings, dissolve the coffee in 1 tsp hot water. Cool. Beat the butter, powdered sugar and cocoa powder in a small bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add the milk and beat until combined. Divide the mixture into 2 portions. Stir the coffee mixture into 1 portion until combined. Add the cocoa powder to the remaining portion.
Spread the chocolate icing over the cooled cupcakes. Let stand until set. Spread the mocha icing over the top. Serve lightly dusted with powdered sugar.

title: raspberry cream strudel
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°F. Grease 2 baking sheets. In a saucepan, bring the milk and vanilla pod to a boil. Remove from heat and allow to stand for 10 mins. Discard vanilla pod.
Meanwhile, beat the egg yolks and sugar in a small bowl until light and fluffy, then stir in the flour.

Whisk milk mixture into egg mixture. Return to saucepan and whisk over low heat until mixture boils and thickens. Remove from heat, cover surface with plastic wrap to prevent a skin forming and allow to cool.
Place a piece of puff pastry on each of the prepared baking sheets. Leaving a 1 inch border around the edges of the remaining 2 pastry pieces, cut slits at 1 inch intervals across their width.

Spread the custard over uncut pastry, leaving a 1 inch border around the edges. Scatter berries evenly over custard. Lightly beat the egg white and brush around the border. Place slit pastry over filling; press edges with a fork to seal.
Brush with egg white and sprinkle with demerara sugar. Bake for 30 mins, or until pastry is browned. Stand for 30 mins before serving.

title: tomato and eggplant stuffed pasta shells
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Toss the eggplant, garlic, chili pepper and oregano with 2 tbsp of the oil. Season with salt and transfer to a baking pan. Roast for 15 mins. Meanwhile, cook the pasta in boiling salted water according to the package directions.

Heat remaining 1 tbsp oil in a medium saucepan on medium heat. Add the bacon and cook until crispy. Drain bacon on paper towels. Add the tomatoes to the saucepan and cook for 1-2 mins. Stir in the tomato paste then the stock. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 5 mins. Add the roasted eggplant and bacon and season with salt, black pepper and a pinch of sugar.
Drain the pasta and arrange on plates. Fill with the eggplant mixture.

title: marinated chili chickens
directions: Blend or process onions, garlic, chilies, vinegar and cumin until almost smooth. Heat oil in a large frying pan. Cook onion mixture, stirring, until fragrant. Add pureed tomatoes and cook, stirring, until mixture boils. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring, for 20 mins, or until thickened. Season.
Brush chicken with 1/2 the chili sauce. Cover and chill for 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 425°F. Place chicken, skin-side up, on an oiled wire rack set in a large shallow baking dish. Roast for 30 mins, or until cooked through.
Serve chicken with remaining chili sauce.

title: rosemary red potatoes
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, combine potatoes, butter, rosemary, onion and salt. Cover and cook on HIGH for 1 min. Stir to coat with melted butter then re-cover and cook for 5 mins. Stir again and cook for an additional 5-6 mins, or until potatoes are tender.
Preheat broiler with an oven rack 6 inches below broiler. Arrange potato mixture on a baking sheet, cut-side up, and broil for 3 mins, or until potatoes are golden. Season with pepper, if desired.

title: pan fried fish with dill potatoes
directions: Bring saucepan of salted water to boil. Add potatoes, cover and cook for 15 mins, or until just tender.
Meanwhile, puree herbs, garlic, lemon juice, capers, and mustard in food processor while pouring extra-virgin oil down spout, until all the oil is blended. Transfer to bowl.
Drain potatoes and, while still warm, add to herb oil and season with salt and pepper.
Heat olive oil in pan on high. Dust fish skin with cornstarch and shake off excess. Cook, skin-side down, for 4-5 mins. Turn and cook for 3-4 mins, until cooked through.
Arrange warm potatoes on plate and place fish on top.

title: bolognese sauce
directions: Heat oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Saute onion, bacon and garlic for 3-4 mins, until tender. Increase heat to high and add ground beef. Cook for 5-6 mins, until browned, breaking up any lumps. Add mushrooms and tomato paste. Cook, stirring, for 1-2 mins. Add tomatoes and wine. Bring to a boil then reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 10-15 mins. Season to taste and stir in parsley.
Toss sauce with drained pasta. Serve topped with shaved Parmesan.

title: roast pork and pineapple salad
directions: Preheat a grill plate over high heat. Lightly coat with oil. Chargrill pineapple for 2-3 mins per side, until tender. Cut slices into quarters.
In a large bowl, combine pork, red cabbage, Chinese cabbage, cilantro, coconut, green onions and pineapple. Set aside.
Meanwhile, to make the sumac dressing, whisk together all ingredients. Season to taste. Drizzle over salad just before serving.

title: piri-piri chicken
directions: Combine garlic, 2/3 of lemon juice, whiskey, bay leaf, paprika, 2 tbsp oil and chicken. Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Combine remaining lemon juice, 1 tbsp oil and onion. Season. Set aside.
Preheat a grill pan over medium heat. Cook chicken for 8-10 mins per side, basting with marinade, until golden and cooked through.
Brush tomatoes, chilies and bread with remaining oil. Cook for 2-3 mins per side, until vegetables are just tender and bread is golden.
Combine piri-piri sauce ingredients. Season.
Top chicken and vegetables with piri-piri sauce. Serve with onion, lemon wedges and bread.

title: plum and blackberry oat crumble
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Bring plums, apples, cinnamon, 3 tbsp brown sugar and 4 tbsp water to a boil then simmer for 5 mins. Transfer to an ovenproof baking dish, remove cinnamon stick and add blackberries.
Place oats, flour and remaining brown sugar in a bowl. Cut in butter until the mixture resembles rough breadcrumbs. Transfer to baking dish and bake for 25-30 mins until topping is crisp and golden.

title: warm strawberries with balsamic zabaglione
directions: Place the strawberries in a medium bowl. Heat the vin santo, honey and sugar in a small saucepan until the sugar dissolves. Pour over the strawberries. Let stand for 10 minutes.

For the zabaglione, beat egg yolks, sugar, balsamic vinegar and vin santo in medium bowl over a medium saucepan of barely simmering water with an electric mixer on medium speed for 5-10 mins or until light and fluffy. (Be careful water doesn't boil too fast or eggs will scramble. Take bowl off the saucepan for 10 seconds, if it gets too hot. Return the bowl to the saucepan, turning down the heat in the process. Use a tea towel to hold bowl when whisking, as it can get warm.)
Divide strawberries among serving glasses and top with zabaglione. Serve with ladyfingers, if desired.

title: moroccan beef and couscous
directions: Bring 2 cups water to boil in a medium saucepan. Add the couscous. Cover and let stand for 5 mins or until liquid is absorbed. Fluff with a fork. Set aside.
Heat a large deep skillet on high heat. Add the ground beef and cook, stirring to break up lumps, for 5 mins or until browned. Add the onion, tomato paste and spice mix; cook and stir for 3 mins.

Stir in the cauliflower, zucchini and 1 cup water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium; cover and simmer for 6 mins or until sauce reduces and vegetables are tender. Stir in chard until wilted. Divide couscous among serving bowls. Top with the meat mixture. Serve with yogurt and lemon wedges.

title: sardines with spiced chickpeas
directions: Pat fish dry, inside and out, with paper towels. Combine lemon juice, paprika, ground cumin, garlic and half the oil in large bowl. Add fish; turn to coat in spice mixture.
Heat an oiled grill pan on high heat or preheat the grill to medium-high. Cook fish until browned both sides and cooked through.

Meanwhile, for the spiced chickpeas, toast cumin seeds, ground coriander and turmeric in medium saucepan on medium heat until fragrant. Stir in remaining oil and chickpeas. Add stock and chili pepper; cook, stirring, until heated through. Remove from heat. Stir in tomatoes and cilantro. Serve with fish.

title: chocolate mint bars
directions: Grease and line a 7x11 inch rimmed baking pan with parchment paper, extending paper 2 inches above long sides.

In a medium heavy-bottomed saucepan over low heat, stir sugar, milk, glucose and butter until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil. Boil, stirring, for 4 mins, or until mixture starts to caramelize and is honey-colored. Remove pan from heat and quickly stir in marshmallows and 9 oz chopped chocolate. Add peppermint oil to taste. Transfer to prepared pan. Spread melted chocolate over top and chill until set. Slice to serve.

title: pork tenderloin stuffed with apple
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line a small roasting pan with parchment paper. In a large frying pan, heat 1 1/2 tbsp butter over medium heat and cook apples for 3-4 mins, stirring, until starting to soften. Add sugar then set aside to cool. Spread over pork tenderloin then roll up and secure with butcher's twine.
Heat remaining butter over medium heat, brown pork for 4-5 mins then transfer to prepared pan and bake for 5-10 mins, or until cooked to your liking. Cover with foil and let rest for 5 mins.

Meanwhile, add shallots and garlic to pan and cook for 2-3 mins, or until tender. Deglaze with wine then bring to a boil, stirring. Add cream and mustard and simmer for 2-3 mins, or until slightly thickened.
Serve stuffed pork tenderloin with shallot pan sauce and mashed potatoes, if desired.

title: ham, cambozola and fig salad with honey mustard dressing
directions: Combine the mustard, honey, oil, lemon juice and vinegar in a screw-top jar and shake well.
Arrange the radicchio, arugula, ham, figs and Cambozola on 4 serving plates. Drizzle with dressing.

title: pear and raspberry bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 180°C/160°C fan/gas 4. Grease and line an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan with parchment paper, extending paper at long sides for handles.

Beat the eggs, vanilla and sugar in a medium bowl with an electric mixer for about 3 mins or until light and creamy. Stir in the flour, ground almonds, butter and buttermilk, then gently fold in the pear and raspberries. Pour the mixture into the prepared pan. Sprinkle with sliced almonds.
Bake for about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan 5 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

title: tofu and cannellini bean patties
directions: Place beans, tofu, breadcrumbs, self-rising flour, green onions, Parmesan cheese, egg, sweet chili sauce, herbs and lemon juice in a food processor and process until combined. Season to taste. Refrigerate for 30 mins, until firm enough to handle.
Using 1/4-cup measure, shape mixture into 8 patties. Dust patties in flour, shaking off excess.
Heat a little oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Fry patties for 1-2 mins each side, until golden. Drain on paper towels. Serve with salad and sweet chili sauce.

title: marble cake with lemon cream and apricots
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease a 11 inch diameter cake pan with oil.

To make the cake, whisk the flour and baking powder together. Using a mixer or electric beaters, mix in the sugar, vanilla extract, eggs, sunflower oil and 1/2 cup water until smooth. Set aside one half the cake mix. Add the cocoa powder into the other half of the cake mix in another bowl.
Begin at the center of the cake pan and add each cake mixture alternatively. Use a toothpick to gently pull the mixtures together. Bake for 35-40 mins, until risen and golden.
Remove the cake from the oven and allow to cool for 10 mins in the pan. Loosen and remove from the cake pan, then leave to cool entirely.

To make the lemon cream, soak the gelatin in cold water for 5 mins. Whip the cream until stiff. Squeeze the excess liquid from the gelatin then place in a small pan over a low heat to melt. Mix the lemon juice and zest into the gelatin, then thoroughly fold it into the whipped cream. Chill for 10 mins.

To assemble the cake, slice the cake in half horizontally and fit a cake ring around the lower half. Spread a third of the lemon cream on the lower half of the cake then arrange the apricot halves on top. Spread the rest of the cream on top the replace the second tier of the cake. Chill for at least 4 hours.

Bring the jam to the boil in a saucepan, pour through a strainer and discard the solids. Remove the cake ring from the cake and brush the jam over the outside of the entire cake. Sprinkle with pistachios and serve.

title: potato and savoy cabbage salad
directions: Cook the potatoes in boiling salted water for 20 mins. Drain, refresh in cold water and cut into slices. Blanch the cabbage in boiling salted water for 4 mins. Use a slotted spoon to transfer to a cold water bath, then drain.
In a saucepan, bring the stock to a boil and stir in the vinegar and mustard. Season to taste, pour over the potatoes and allow to stand for 20 mins.

Heat the oil in a frying pan and saute the mushrooms for 2 mins. Season to taste. Fold mushrooms and cabbage into the potatoes and allow to stand for 10 mins. Fold in the radishes and parsley and season to taste.

title: cherry jubilee jello
directions: Combine sugar and 3/4 cup water in a medium saucepan. Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves. Simmer for 10 mins, or until syrup is thicker but still clear. Add gelatin and stir until dissolved. Stir in brandy. Let cool for 10 mins, skimming any scum from surface.
Transfer mixture to a greased 10x3 inch loaf pan. Chill for 3 hours, or until firm.
Turn jello out onto a clean cutting board and cut into squares with a hot, wet knife.

title: hearty sausage frittata
directions: Steam the potatoes, cauliflower and pumpkin over a saucepan of boiling water 8 mins or until just tender. Whisk the eggs, milk, cheese and onions in a bowl. Season.

Preheat broiler to high. Heat the oil in a 2 x 10 inch round ovenproof frying pan over medium heat. Add the sausages. Cook about 8 mins, turning, until cooked through. Remove from the pan and slice thickly. Return to pan and reduce the heat to low. Add the steamed vegetables and stir to combine. Pour in the egg mixture, stir, cover and cook 10 mins or until almost set. Remove the lid, transfer to the oven and broil 2 mins until golden and set. Serve with the bread and mixed greens.

title: chewy muesli cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Grease and line 2 baking pans with parchment paper.
Combine oats, flour, sugar, cinnamon, dried fruit and nuts in large bowl.

Melt butter with golden syrup in small saucepan on low heat. Add combined baking soda and 1 tbsp boiling water. Stir warm butter mixture into dry ingredients. Roll level tablespoons of mixture into balls. Place 2 inches apart on prepared pans; flatten with hand.
Bake about 20 mins. Cool in pan 2 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

title: chicken, corn and noodle soup
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan on medium heat. Cook onion, garlic and ginger, stirring, for about 5 mins or until the onion is soft.
Add stock, 2 cups water and both corns to the pan. Cover and bring to a boil on high heat.
Add the white parts of the green onions to the pan. Reduce the heat to medium-low. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 mins.
Carefully break the noodles in half and add to the pan. Simmer, uncovered, for about 2 mins. Stir to separate the noodles.
Add chicken to pan and simmer, uncovered, about 1 min or until the chicken is cooked through. Add soy sauce to taste, if needed.
Stir in the spinach. Divide soup among four serving bowls. Sprinkle with remaining green onions.

title: rabbit stew with morels, scallions and dumplings
directions: Soak the morels in 1 cup of water for 2-3 hours.

Season the rabbit to taste. Heat the butter in a dutch oven and fry the bacon and onions until the onions are translucent. Fry the rabbit pieces, turning as necessary until they're golden brown all over. Add the wine and chicken stock, covered and simmer over medium heat for 20 mins.
Drain the morels add them to the rabbit stew, along with the cream. Simmer for another 20 minutes.
Add the scallions and stir well. Bring to a boil, stir in the cornstarch and lemon juice and season to taste.

For the dumplings: whisk the eggs with 1/2 cup of water, a pinch of salt and the nutmeg. Stir in the flour using a hand mixer. Knead the dough until it is smooth and tiny blisters appear just below the surface. On a floured surface, roll the dough into small noodles and drop them directly into boiling salt water. Cook for 3-4 mins. Drain and serve the dumplings with the rabbit stew.

title: tamarind soy sauce
directions: Heat the oil in a small saucepan on medium heat. Cook the garlic, stirring, until fragrant. Add the soy sauce, sugar, tamarind, ginger and 1/3 cup water.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, for about 2 mins or until the sauce thickens. Remove from heat. Stir in the onion.

title: warm salami and tomato pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta according to package instructions. Drain, rinse under cold water and drain again.
In large frying pan, cook the salami, stirring, over medium heat for about 5 mins or until crisp. Drain on a paper towel.
In a large bowl, combine the pasta, salami, nuts, tomatoes, herbs and cheese and toss gently to combine.
To make the vinaigrette, place the ingredients in a screw-top jar, season to taste and shake well.
Pour vinaigrette over salad and toss gently to coat.

title: mini party pizzas
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°F. Line 2 baking pans with parchment paper.
Cut eight 3-inch rounds, hearts or other shapes from each pizza crust using cookie cutters. Place shapes on prepared pans.
Spread with pizza sauce and decorate to make faces. Sprinkle with mozzarella.
Bake for 10-15 mins, until crusts are crisp and cheese has melted.

title: fruity cake squares
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan and line with parchment paper.
Combine brown sugar, butter and syrup in a medium saucepan on medium heat. Stir until sugar has dissolved. Add dried fruit and spices. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and cool for 10 mins.

Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Spread evenly in prepared pan. Sprinkle with fruit mixture and then almonds. Bake for 25-30 mins, until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool completely in pan on wire rack.

For the icing, combine powdered sugar and 2 tsp hot water in a small bowl. If desired, add a few drops red food color to tint icing pink. Drizzle over cooled cake. Cut into squares to serve. Store in an airtight container.

title: spaghetti bolognaise
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Cook and stir onions, garlic and bacon for 3-4 mins. Stir in celery and cook and stir for 2 mins.

Add ground beef and cook, stirring with a wooden spoon to break up lumps, for 5 mins, or until browned. Stir in stock, tomatoes, tomato paste and bay leaves. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 30 mins, or until sauce has thickened. Remove bay leaves.
Meanwhile, cook pasta in plenty of boiling salted water for 10-12 mins according to pack instructions, or until tender but firm to the bite then drain.
Place pasta in serving bowls, spoon meat sauce over, top with Parmesan. Serve.

title: lamb biryani
directions: Combine ginger, garlic, chilies, spices and mint. Add lamb and toss to coat. Cover with plastic wrap and chill for at least 3 hours.

Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Cook onions, stirring, for 8-10 mins, or until golden brown. Set aside. Increase heat to high. Working in batches, cook lamb for 2 mins, or until seared. Return all lamb to pan along with bay leaves and yogurt. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30-40 mins, or until lamb is tender. Season.

Add rice and 2 cups water. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 mins, or until rice is tender and liquid absorbed. Remove from heat and let cool slightly. Serve with reserved yogurt and mint.

title: grilled fish with cilantro citrus butter
directions: For the cilantro citrus butter, combine butter, cilantro, ginger, orange peel and ground coriander in a bowl. Spoon into a log on a piece of plastic wrap. Roll up tightly, twisting ends to seal. Freeze for 30 mins or until firm.
Place couscous in a medium bowl and add 1 1/4 cups boiling water. Cover and let stand for about 10 mins. After liquid has been absorbed, mix couscous with a fork.
Heat a grill pan on high heat. Drizzle fish with oil. Cook for 2-3 mins each side, or until browned and cooked through.
Spoon couscous and vegetables onto serving plates. Top with fish. Slice butter log. Place a slice on fish to melt before serving.

title: lemon burst cookie sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line 2 baking sheets with parchment. Using an electric mixer, beat butter, powdered sugar, zest and juice in a bowl until light and creamy. Add flour and cornstarch; stir to combine.

Place mixture into a piping bag fitted with 1/2-inch fluted nozzle; pipe 40 rounds onto prepared trays, leaving room for spreading. Bake for 10 minutes or until golden. Cool on trays (cookies will firm).
Spread lemon curd over base of half the cookies. Sandwich with remaining cookies. Dust with extra powdered sugar to serve.

title: cherry and apricot smoothie
directions: In a food processor, puree cherries, apricots and juice, honey and mint until smooth.
Fill 4 chilled glasses with ice. Pour pureed fruit over top. Serve immediately, decorated with mint sprigs.

title: red curry pilau with sausages
directions: Heat olive oil in a large saucepan on high. Saute onion, celery, pepper, red curry paste, chili and garlic for 2-3 minutes, until vegetables are tender and mixture is aromatic.
Mix in basmati rice, chicken stock, cherry tomatoes and white wine. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered for 15-20 minutes, until all liquid is absorbed.
Stir in sausage and season to taste. Cook, stirring, for 1-2 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with parsley.

title: tuscan bread soup
directions: Heat the oil in a large saucepan on medium heat. Saute the carrot, onion and celery for 3-4 mins, until tender. Stir in the tomato paste.
Add the stock, cabbage and potato. Bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to low; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 20 mins.
Add the remaining vegetables and cannellini beans. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 mins. Add the bread. Simmer for 3 mins. Season to taste.
Cook bacon in a small skillet until crisp. Serve the soup topped with bacon, shaved Parmesan cheese and freshly ground black pepper.

title: chocolate dipped marshmallows
directions: Combine chocolate, cream and butter in a heat-resistant bowl. Place bowl over saucepan of simmering water (do not allow water to touch base of bowl). Let stand until chocolate has melted and mixture is smooth, stirring occasionally.
Insert a pop stick into each marshmallow.
To serve, dip marshmallows in chocolate mixture then roll in sprinkles or toasted coconut.

title: open faced burgers
directions: Combine ground beef, breadcrumbs, egg and 2 tbsp pesto. Shape into 4 patties. Heat 1 tbsp oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Cook patties for 3-4 mins per side, or until browned and cooked through. Transfer to a baking tray.
Add remaining oil to pan. Cook onion for 2-3 mins, or until golden. Set aside.

Preheat broiler. Toast focaccia under broiler until golden. Set aside. Sprinkle beef patties with cheese. Broil until cheese bubbles and melts. Whisk together mayonnaise and remaining pesto. Spread 1/2 over focaccia then place 1 piece of focaccia on each serving plate. Top with spinach, tomatoes, onions and beef patties. Top with remaining pesto mayonnaise. Serve with potato wedges.

title: chicken braised in milk with lemon
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Rub chicken with nutmeg and season. Heat oil in a roasting pan, add chicken and saute over medium-high heat, turning frequently until browned all over. Place garlic and lemon slices around chicken and pour milk over top. Cover with foil and bake for about 1 hour. Uncover, sprinkle with lemon zest and cook for another 30-45 mins until chicken is golden brown and juices run clear when thickest part of thigh is pierced.

title: flag waving layered drink
directions: In a bowl, steep raspberries in grenadine syrup for 15 mins. Divide among 6 serving glasses. Add ice cubes to fill glasses 2/3 full. Stir together seltzer and triple sec. Divide among glasses. Top with blueberries.

title: pork and beans in tomato sauce
directions: Heat the oil in a large, deep ovenproof frying pan. Add the pork and sear on both sides for a few mins. Season with salt, pepper. Transfer to a baking dish and set aside.

Add the potatoes to the pan and fry a few mins until golden. Add the onion and peppers and saute briefly. Stir in the canned tomatoes, breaking them up with a spoon. Add the tomato juice and beans. Bring to a boil, season well and simmer 15 mins.

Preheat the oven to 400°F. Add the beans and sauce to the baking dish with the meat. Mix the cheese and sour cream and spoon in dollops on top. Cook for about 25 mins until the meat is tender, then sprinkle with parsley to serve.

title: bangladeshi lamb curry
directions: Heat ghee in a large, heavy-bottomed frying pan over high heat. Cook onions and spices for 8-10 mins, stirring, until golden brown. Add garlic and ginger. Cook for 1 min, until fragrant. Add lamb and cook for 4-5 mins, to brown all over. Add sugar and cayenne. Stir in yogurt, 1 tbsp at a time, stirring between each addition. Season. Bring to a boil then reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 1 hour, or until lamb is tender.
Add beans and simmer for 2 mins. Serve over rice, topped with sliced almonds and sliced red chili.

title: mashed potatoes with bacon and arugula
directions: In a large saucepan over high heat, bring potatoes, garlic and salted water (enough to cover the potatoes) to a boil. Cook for 15 mins or until potatoes are fork-tender. Drain potatoes well and return to saucepan and garlic.

Meanwhile, in a skillet over medium-high heat, cook bacon for 4 mins or until crisp, turning once. Drain bacon on paper towels and crumble. Remove all but 1 tablespoon bacon drippings from skillet. Add arugula to bacon drippings in skillet. Cook for 1 min or just until wilted. Remove from the heat.

Using hand masher or potato ricer, mash potatoes and garlic with vegetable broth, milk and butter until smooth, adding additional milk if desired. Stir in arugula and crumbled bacon. Season to taste with salt and ground black pepper, if desired.

title: no-bake cookies and coffee cake
directions: Heat milk and coffee in a saucepan until lukewarm. Transfer to a heatproof bowl. Dip cookies lightly, one by one, into coffee mixture, then arrange 8 cookies on a serving plate to form an 8 x 6 inch rectangle. Sprinkle with a little of the cocoa powder. Repeat using remaining cookies, milk mixture and remaining cocoa powder to make 4 layers in total.

Using an electric mixer, beat cream cheese and butter in a bowl until very light and creamy. Beat in combined sifted powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons of the extra cocoa powder until combined. Spread over top of cake. Chill for 15 minutes.
Serve cookie cake dusted with remaining extra cocoa powder.

title: raspberry cheese crumble
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. For the raspberry compote, mix 1/4 cup of cornstarch with 1/4 cup of water. Bring the cherry juice to a boil with 1 tbsp of sugar and thicken it with the cornstarch mixture. Stir in the raspberries and cool.

For the crumble mixture, mix the flour, butter, brown sugar, salt and vanilla extract in a large mixing bowl with the dough hook of a mixer, then rub the mixture together with your fingers to crumble.
For the cheese mixture, mix the eggs and cream with a whisk and add the remaining cornstarch, the cream cheese and the remaining sugar.

To assemble, put 2/3 of the crumble mix into a greased 10 x 12 baking sheet and press it down with your fingers. Spread it with stripes of the cheese mixture and fill in the gaps with stripes of raspberry compote. Sprinkle with the remaining crumble mixture and bake for about 45 mins. Cool and cut into pieces. Serve dusted with powdered sugar.

title: macaroni and cheese with tuna
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salted water for 10-12 mins or until al dente, adding broccoli and pea-and-corn mix for the last 2 mins. Drain.

Meanwhile, melt butter in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add flour then gradually add milk, stirring. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 mins or until sauce thickens. Add cheese then toss with pasta and tuna. Season then transfer to a baking dish.
Preheat broiler. Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over pasta. Broil for 3-4 mins, or until golden brown. Serve immediately.

title: potatoes in garlic sauce
directions: Cook the potatoes in boiling, salted water for 15-20 mins until tender. Meanwhile, toast the bread then place in a bowl of cold water.

Heat 1 tbsp of the oil in a medium skillet on medium-high heat. Saute the onion and garlic for 4-6 mins. Remove the bread from the water and break into pieces. Add the bread, almonds, parsley and cayenne pepper to the skillet and continue to cook for 2-3 mins.

Transfer the mixture to a food processor. Add remaining 5 tbsp oil and season. Process until sauce is smooth. Add water if the mixture is too thick. Transfer the sauce to a serving plate and top with potatoes. Serve.

title: pepper steak with onion gratin
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Melt 2 tbsp of butter in a saucepan. Add the flour and cook briefly. Whisk in the stock and the milk, bring to a boil, and keep it at a rolling boil for 5 mins. Season to taste then melt the cheese into the sauce. Divide the onion wedges evenly between 4 small ramekins then distribute the sauce over top. Bake for 1 hour.

Meanwhile, coat the steaks in the crushed black peppercorns. Heat the oil in a large pan and sear the steaks for about 7 mins, turning as necessary. Remove the steaks from the pan, wrap in aluminum foil and set aside to rest. Add the diced onions to the pan and saute until translucent. Add the cognac and 2 tbsp of cold butter. Serve the steaks and gratin garnished with the sauce and thyme.

title: roasted pears with honey and cinnamon
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Line a roasting pan with parchment paper. Arrange pears in a single layer in prepared dish, cut side down. Scatter lemon peel and cinnamon over top.

Combine 3/4 cup water, honey and sugar, stirring to dissolve then pour over pears. Cover tightly with foil and bake 15-20 mins. Remove foil and turn pears over. Bake, uncovered, for 15-20 mins, basting with syrup, until just tender. Serve with yogurt or ice-cream.

title: pepper and spinach orzo
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add mushrooms and cook, stirring, for 8 mins, or until tender. Add garlic and stock. Bring to a boil then add orzo. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 10-12 mins, or until orzo is al dente and liquid is almost absorbed.

Add peppers and spinach. Cook for 2 mins, or until spinach wilts. Remove from heat and let stand for 2 mins. Add 1/2 the ricotta, parsley and lemon zest. Distribute between serving bowls and sprinkle with remaining ricotta, parsley and lemon zest.

title: peach cream pastries
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Line a baking tray with parchment paper and lay the pastry squares on it with at least 1 inch space between them. Brush with the egg wash and sprinkle with the sugar. Bake for 10-12 mins, until golden. Allow to cool on a wire rack.
Beat the cream, creme fraiche and vanilla extract with a whisk. In a saucepan, heat the jam, stirring, until smooth.

Cut the pastry squares in half horizontally. Arrange the peaches over the bottom halves, drizzle over the jam and sprinkle with the amaretti. Spoon over the cream mixture and top with the pastry lids.

title: almond crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and line 2 baking trays with parchment paper.

Combine ground almonds, sugar, lemon zest and vanilla in a large bowl. Add egg whites and stir until combined. Place sliced almonds in a small bowl. Roll level tbsp of mixture in sliced almonds. Roll into 3 1/2 inch logs and shape into crescents. Press any remaining almonds on top.
Place on prepared trays and bake for 15 mins, or until lightly browned. Let cool on trays. Serve.

title: seafood medley with dipping sauce
directions: To make the dipping sauce, combine the sour cream, mayonnaise and ketchup in a small bowl. Season to taste, then refrigerate

Preheat the oven to 425°F. Line a baking tray with parchment paper. Next, place the beaten eggs in a small bowl, then combine the breadcrumbs and parmesan in another wide-rimmed bowl. Put the fish and flour in a large, resealable, food storage bag. Seal the bag to secure then shake gently to coat the fish evenly in flour.

Dip the fish in the egg, letting any excess egg drain off, then toss the fish in the breadcrumb mixture to coat lightly. Place the fish on the prepared baking tray in a single layer. Cover the fish with plastic wrap and chill for 15 mins.
Arrange the calamari and potato wedges on another baking tray. Bake for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown and cooked through.
Meanwhile, spray the fish with oil, then bake in the oven for 10 mins. Turn the fish over and bake for 10 mins more or until golden and cooked through.
Serve the fish, calamari and potatoes in baskets or bowls with dipping sauce and lemon wedges.

title: mini bacon meatloaves
directions: Preheat the oven 400°F. Line a baking pan with foil.
Place ground beef, onion, zucchini, sauces, egg and breadcrumbs in a large bowl. Using clean hands, mix until well combined. Shape into 2 oval meatloaves. Place on prepared pan.
Wrap each loaf with bacon; secure with toothpicks. Place tomato on pan with meatloaves. Drizzle with oil and sprinkle with freshly ground black pepper.
Bake for 20-25 mins or until meatloaves are cooked through. Remove toothpicks. Serve with roasted tomato, mashed sweet potato and peas.

title: chicken breasts with salad and peanut sauce
directions: Heat 1-2 tbsp of oil in a pan and fry the chicken breasts for 10 mins, turning as necessary. Season them to taste, remove from the pan and set aside to cool. Heat 1 tbsp of oil in a pan and saute the shallots and garlic. Add the peanut butter and stir it until it melts. Add 1/2-1/3 cup water and stir the mixture into a smooth sauce. Season with the soy sauce, sambal oelek, 1 tbsp lemon juice and 1/2 tsp of sugar. Set the sauce aside to cool, stirring occasionally.
Arrange 4-8 lettuce leaves on 4 plates and cut the rest into strips. Cut the chicken breasts into thin slices.

For the lemon dressing, mix 3 tbsp of lemon juice with salt, pepper and 1/2 tsp of sugar. Mix in 2-3 tbsp of oil and toss the lettuce strips, scallion, carrot and cucumber with the lemon dressing. Serve the salad in the lettuce leaves with the chicken slices, topped with peanut sauce and garnished with the chopped peanuts.

title: roasted squash salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. On a sheet pan, toss squash with olive oil and season. Roast for 20 mins. Let cool.

Meanwhile, in a bowl, whisk together raspberry vinaigrette, shallot and Dijon mustard. Divide salad greens, red onion, roasted squash, pomegranate seeds, scallions and pine nuts between 8 serving plates. Drizzle with vinaigrette.

title: pan-seared white fish with warm tomato salad and pesto
directions: Drizzle the fish with lemon juice. Heat the butter in a frying pan, add the onions and fish and fry for 5-7 mins, covered.
To make the pesto, place the basil, Parmesan, half the garlic, oil and pine nuts in a food processor and puree briefly.

Remove the fish from the pan. Add the remaining garlic and tomatoes to the pan and saute for 1-2 mins. Season with salt and pepper. Divide the tomatoes between 4 plates and top with the fish. Drizzle with pesto then serve.

title: chicken, bacon and mushroom risotto
directions: In a large saucepan, heat the oil and saute the mushrooms and green onion for 1 min, then remove from the pan and set aside.
Add the chicken, bacon and garlic, then cook for 3-4 mins until just colored. Remove from the pan and set aside.
Add the rice to the pan with the butter and toss to coat the grains. Toast for 1-2 mins. Add the chicken mixture, along with 1 cup of stock.
When the stock has absorbed, add another 1 cup and continue to simmer. Next, gently stir in the remaining stock. It will take about 15-20 mins for the rice to become tender.
Stir in the mushroom mixture, cream and parmesan, and heat through.
Serve with a sprinkling of chopped chives and toasted pine nuts.

title: caramel banana pinwheels
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease an 8-inch round baking pan; sprinkle bottom of pan with 2 tbsp of the sugar.

Place flours and 1 tbsp of the remaining sugar in medium bowl; rub in butter. Mash one of the bananas; add to bowl with milk. Mix to a soft, sticky dough. Knead dough on floured surface. Roll dough to 16 x 12-inch rectangle.
Chop remaining bananas finely. Sprinkle remaining sugar over dough; top with nuts and banana.
Starting from long side, roll dough tightly; trim ends. Cut roll into 10 slices. Place pinwheels, cut-side up, in single layer, in pan.
Bake pinwheels about 30 mins. Serve warm.

title: lamb flatbreads
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet on high heat. Brown ground lamb for 4-5 mins, breaking up lumps. Stir in seeds and spices and cook for 1-2 mins, until seeds are toasted. Add honey and cook for 30 seconds. Remove from heat and season to taste.
For the salad, combine all ingredients in a bowl. Season to taste.
Spread flatbreads with hummus. Cover evenly with lamb mixture, then top with a handful of salad to serve.

title: garlic soup with croutons
directions: For the croutons, heat 4 tbsp oil in a skillet and toast the cubed bread for 5 mins until golden. Set aside.

Heat the remaining oil in a pot and sweat the garlic, onion and chili over low-medium heat for 5 mins. Add the sugar and bell peppers and lightly caramelize. Add the stock, cover and simmer for 20 mins. Add the tomato and croutons and cook for an additional 10 mins. Serve sprinkled with parsley.

title: raspberry macadamia blondies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly grease an 8-inch square cake pan and line base and sides with parchment paper, extending paper 1 inch above edges.
Place butter and half the chocolate in a medium saucepan and melt over low heat, stirring. Cool for 10 mins.

Stir in flour, sugar, eggs, macadamias and remaining chocolate. Fold in raspberries, then spread into prepared pan. Bake for 25-30 mins, until a skewer comes out clean. Cool in pan. Dust with powdered sugar and cut into squares to serve.

title: tuna and zucchini pasta
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salted water until al dente then drain and set aside.

Meanwhile, melt butter. Add flour and cook until light brown and nutty. Add stock and stir over low heat until sauce begins to thicken. Add cream cheese, chives and marjoram. Season. Set aside and keep warm.
Heat oil in a separate pan and saute zucchini for about 3 mins, add garlic and cook for 2 mins. Season and add tuna to warm through. Toss with sauce and pasta and serve immediately.

title: olive, sun-dried tomato and bacon rolls with baked potatoes and yogurt dip
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Toss potatoes with 4 tbsp oil and 1 tsp sea salt. Transfer to a baking tray and bake for 45 mins.
For yogurt dip, mix yogurt, mayonnaise and garlic. Season.

Wrap a slice of bacon around each olive then wrap a slice of remaining bacon around every 2 sun-dried tomatoes. Heat 2 tbsp oil in a frying pan and saute bacon rolls until browned and crispy. Remove from pan and stick a toothpick into each.
To serve, remove potatoes from oven and sprinkle with chives and 1/2 tsp sea salt. Serve with bacon rolls, garnished with mixed salad greens, olives and yogurt dip.

title: spiced fruit strudel
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Grease a baking pan and line with parchment paper. Combine peaches, nectarines, brown sugar, raisins, spices and breadcrumbs in medium bowl.

Stack phyllo sheets, brushing between sheets with half the combined butter and milk. Cut stack in half widthwise. Cover one stack with parchment paper, then with a damp tea towel, to prevent drying out.

Place half the fruit mixture along center of uncovered phyllo stack. Roll from one side to enclose filling, sealing ends of roll with a little of the remaining butter mixture. Place strudel, seam-side down, on prepared pan. Brush all over with a little of the remaining butter mixture. Repeat process with remaining phyllo stack, fruit mixture and butter mixture.
Bake for 25 mins, or until browned. Cut each strudel in half. Dust with sifted powdered sugar.

title: apple and custard muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F. Grease a 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners.

Combine butter, flour, 1/2 tsp cinnamon, sugar, egg and milk in large bowl. Stir until just combined. Distribute 1/2 of the batter between paper liners then add 1 tsp custard and 2 tsp apple pie filling to each. Top with remaining batter. Combine brown sugar and remaining cinnamon.
